478 //Parse filename and extract one for given optics type in combined runs
479 QString US_Analysis_auto::get_filename( QString triple_name )
480 {
481  qDebug() << "FileName -- " << FileName;
482  qDebug() << "triple_name -- " << triple_name;
483 
484  QString filename_parsed;
485 
486  if ( FileName.contains(",") && FileName.contains("IP") && FileName.contains("RI") )
487  {
488  QStringList fileList = FileName.split(",");
489 
490  //Interference
491  if ( triple_name.contains("Interference") )
492  {
493  for (int i=0; i<fileList.size(); ++i )
494  {
495  QString fname = fileList[i];
496  int pos = fname.lastIndexOf(QChar('-'));
497  qDebug() << "IP: pos -- " << pos;
498  qDebug() << "IP: fname.mid( pos ) -- " << fname.mid( pos );
499  if ( fname.mid( pos ) == "-IP")
500  {
501  filename_parsed = fname;
502  break;
503  }
504  }
505  }
506  //UV/vis.
507  else
508  {
509  for (int i=0; i<fileList.size(); ++i )
510  {
511  QString fname = fileList[i];
512  int pos = fname.lastIndexOf(QChar('-'));
513  qDebug() << "RI: pos -- " << pos;
514  qDebug() << "RI: fname.mid( pos ) -- " << fname.mid( pos );
515  if ( fname.mid( pos ) == "-RI")
516  {
517  filename_parsed = fname;
518  break;
519  }
520  }
521  }
522  }
523  else
524  filename_parsed = FileName;
525 
526  qDebug() << "Parsed filename: " << filename_parsed;
527 
528  return filename_parsed;
529 }

531 //Gui update: timer's slot
532 void US_Analysis_auto::gui_update( )
533 {
534  //qDebug() << "in_gui_update: " << in_gui_update;
535 
536  if ( in_gui_update ) // If already doing a reload,
537  return; // skip starting a new one
538 
539  in_gui_update = true; // Flag in the midst of a reload
540 
541  /**** JSON structure ****************************************************************/
542  /*
543 
544  {
545  "to_process":["2DSA_MC",".."],
546  "processed" :[
547  {"2DSA" :{"gfacID":"17","status":"COMPLETE","statusMsg":"Finished: maxrss 441 MB, total run seconds 48"}},
548  {"2DSA_FM":{"gfacID":"18","status":"COMPLETE","statusMsg":"Finished: maxrss 462 MB, total run seconds 32"}},
549  {"FITMEN" :{"gfacID":null,"status":"COMPLETE","statusMsg":"Waiting for manual stage FITMEN to complete."}}
550  ],
551  "submitted":"2DSA_IT"
552  }
553 
554  */
555 
556  US_Passwd pw;
557  US_DB2 db( pw.getPasswd() );
558 
559  // Get the buffer data from the database
560  if ( db.lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
561  {
562  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "Connection Problem" ),
563  tr( "Could not connect to database \n" ) + db.lastError() );
564  return;
565  }
566 
567 
568 
569  /*************** GUI UPDATE *************************************************************/
570  QMap<QString, QMap <QString, QString> >::iterator jj;
571  for ( jj = Array_of_analysis.begin(); jj != Array_of_analysis.end(); ++jj )
572  {
573  QString triple_current = jj.key();
574  QString triple_curr_key = jj.key();
575  QString triple_curr = triple_current.replace("."," / ");
576 
577 
578  qDebug() << "triple_curr_key, triple_curr: " << triple_curr_key << ", " << triple_curr;
579 
580  QMap <QString, QString > ana_details = jj.value();
581 
582  QString requestID = ana_details["requestID"];
583 
584  QMap <QString, QString > current_analysis_details;
585  current_analysis_details = read_autoflowAnalysis_record( &db, requestID );
586 
587  if ( !current_analysis_details.size() )
588  {

1125  lineedit_lastupd -> setText( update_time );
1126 
1127  //cluster
1128  lineedit_cluster -> setText( cluster );
1129 
1130 
1131  //if complete
1132  if ( status == "COMPLETE" )
1133  {
1134  pb_overlay->setEnabled( true );
1135  pb_delete->setEnabled( false );
1136  lineedit_status -> setStyleSheet( "QLineEdit { background-color: rgb(2, 88, 57); color : white; }");
1137 
1138  // && if final stage
1139  if ( !to_process_array.size() )
1140  {
1141  topItem [ triple_curr ] -> setForeground( 0, QBrush( colorGreen ) );
1142  /****
1143  ALEXEY: maybe update QMap < triple_curr , bool > Completed_triples with TRUE (defined as all FALSES at the beginning):
1144  Completed_triples[ triple_curr ] = true;
1145  At the end of update cycle over triples, check if there is at least one FALSE value in the Completed_triple QMap.
1146  If NO - stop timer, show Msg that everything completed.
1147  **/
1148 
1150  //Completed_triples[ triple_curr_key ] = true; // May cause race conditions!!!!
1151  /*******************************************************************************************/
1152 
1153  qDebug() << "set Completed_triples[ " << triple_curr_key << " ] to " << Completed_triples[ triple_curr_key ];
1154 
1155  }
1156  }
1157 
1158  //check if failed -- due to the abortion/deletion of the job
1159  if ( status == "FAILED" || status == "failed" || status == "CANCELED" || status == "canceled")
1160  {
1161  pb_overlay->setEnabled( false );
1162  pb_delete->setEnabled( false );
1163  lineedit_status -> setStyleSheet( "QLineEdit { background-color: rgb(210, 0, 0); color : white; }");
1164  topItem [ triple_curr ] -> setForeground( 0, QBrush( colorRed ));
1165 
1167  //Completed_triples[ triple_curr_key ] = true;
1168  /*******************************************************************************************/
1169 
1170  if ( status == "FAILED" || status == "failed" )
1171  {
1172  Failed_triples [ triple_curr_key ] = true;
1173  qDebug() << "FAILED status for triple/stage -- " << triple_curr_key << "/" << submitted.toString();
1174  }
1175  if ( status == "CANCELED" || status == "canceled")
1176  {
1177  Canceled_triples [ triple_curr_key ] = true;
1178  qDebug() << "CANCELED status for triple/stage -- " << triple_curr_key << "/" << submitted.toString();
1179  }
1180  }
1181  }
1182  }
1183  }
1184 
1185  // Check if all triples completed //
1186  all_processed = true;
1187  QMap<QString, bool>::iterator td;
1188  for ( td = Completed_triples.begin(); td != Completed_triples.end(); ++td )
1189  {
1190  qDebug() << "Key/Value of Completed_triples: " << td.key() << "/" << td.value();
1191  if ( !td.value() )
1192  {
1193  all_processed = false;
1194  break;
1195  }
1196  }
1197  qDebug() << "all_processed: " << all_processed;
1198 
1199  //check if there are failed triples
1200  bool failed_triples = false;
1201  QStringList Failed_triples_list;
1202 
1203  QMap<QString, bool>::iterator tdf;
1204  for ( tdf = Failed_triples.begin(); tdf != Failed_triples.end(); ++tdf )
1205  {
1206  qDebug() << "Key/Value of Failed_triples: " << tdf.key() << "/" << tdf.value();
1207  if ( tdf.value() )
1208  {
1209  Failed_triples_list << tdf.key();
1210  failed_triples = true;
1211  }
1212  }
1213  qDebug() << "Failed_triples exist ? Name(s): " << failed_triples << Failed_triples_list;
1214 
1215  //check if there are canceled triples
1216  bool canceled_triples = false;
1217  QStringList Canceled_triples_list;
1218 
1219  QMap<QString, bool>::iterator tdc;
1220  for ( tdc = Canceled_triples.begin(); tdc != Canceled_triples.end(); ++tdc )
1221  {
1222  qDebug() << "Key/Value of Canceled_triples: " << tdc.key() << "/" << tdc.value();
1223  if ( tdc.value() )
1224  {
1225  Canceled_triples_list << tdc.key();
1226  canceled_triples = true;
1227  }
1228  }
1229  qDebug() << "Canceled_triples exist ? Name(s): " << canceled_triples << Canceled_triples_list;
1230 
1231 
1232  //If all triples processed, show msg && Stop update timer
1233  if ( all_processed )
1234  {
1235  //stop timer
1236  if ( timer_update -> isActive() )
1237  {
1238  timer_update -> stop();
1239  disconnect(timer_update, SIGNAL(timeout()), 0, 0);
1240 
1241  qDebug() << "Update stopped upon final completion...";
1242  }
1243 
1244  QString msg_text = "All triples have been processed.";
1245 
1246  if ( failed_triples )
1247  msg_text += QString("\n\nNOTE: analyses for the following triples FAILED: \n\n%1").arg( Failed_triples_list.join(", ") );
1248 
1249  if ( canceled_triples )
1250  msg_text += QString("\n\nNOTE: analyses for the following triples have been CANCELED: \n\n%1").arg( Canceled_triples_list.join(", ") );
1251 
1252  msg_text += QString("\n\nThe program will proceed to the Reporting stage. ");
1253 
1254  //Update autoflow record at Analysis completion
1255  update_autoflow_record_atAnalysis();
1256 
1257  if ( failed_triples || canceled_triples )
1258  {
1259  QMessageBox::information( this,
1260  tr( "All Triples Processed !" ),
1261  msg_text );
1262  }
1263 
1264  in_gui_update = false;
1265 
1266  //ALEXEY: Append with info on failed triples when bad_meniscus values:
1267  protocol_details_at_analysis[ "failed" ] = "";
1268 
1269  //ALEXEY: Switch to next stage (Report)
1270  emit analysis_complete_auto( protocol_details_at_analysis );
1271  }
1272 
1273  in_gui_update = false;
1274 }

1337 //Load rawData/editedData

1339 {
1340  rawData.clear();
1341  editedData.clear();
1342 
1343  US_Passwd pw;
1344  US_DB2* db = new US_DB2( pw.getPasswd() );
1345 
1346  if ( db->lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
1347  {
1348  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
1349  QMessageBox::information( this,
1350  tr( "DB Connection Problem" ),
1351  tr( "There was an error connecting to the database:\n" )

1353

1359  int eID=0;

1366 
1367  qDebug() << "In loadData() Query: " << query;

1376 
1377  while ( db->next() )

1390  if ( time_to_now < latest_update_time )
1391  {
1392  latest_update_time = time_to_now;

1394

1396  eID = editedDataID;
1397  efilename = filename;
1398  }
1399  }
1400  }
1401 
1402  qDebug() << "In loadData() after Query ";
1403

1406  if (!edir.exists())
1407  edir.mkpath( edirpath );
1408

1410

1412

1415  // QFileInfo check_file( efilepath );
1416  // if ( check_file.exists() && check_file.isFile() )
1417  // qDebug() << "EditProfile file: " << efilepath << " exists";
1418  // else
1419  db->readBlobFromDB( efilepath, "download_editData", eID );
1420 
1421  qDebug() << "In loadData() after readBlobFromDB ";
1422 
1423  //Now download rawData corresponding to rID:
1424  QString efilename_copy = efilename;
1425  QStringList efilename_copy_list = efilename_copy.split(".");
1426

1428  + efilename_copy_list[3] + "."
1429  + efilename_copy_list[4] + "."
1430  + efilename_copy_list[5] + ".auc";
1431

1433  //do we need to check for existance ?
1434  db->readBlobFromDB( rfilepath, "download_aucData", rID );
1435 
1436  qApp->processEvents();
1437

1439 
1440  //Put downloaded data in memory:
1441  QString uresdir = US_Settings::resultDir() + "/" + triple_information[ "filename" ] + "/";
1442  US_DataIO::loadData( uresdir, efilename, editedData, rawData );
1443 
1444  eID_global = eID;
1445

1452 bool US_Analysis_auto::loadModel( QMap < QString, QString > & triple_information )
1453 {
1454  US_Passwd pw;
1455  US_DB2* db = new US_DB2( pw.getPasswd() );
1456 
1457  if ( db->lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
1458  {
1459  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
1460  QMessageBox::information( this,
1461  tr( "DB Connection Problem" ),
1462  tr( "There was an error connecting to the database:\n" )
1463  + db->lastError() );
1464 
1465  return false;
1466  }
1467 
1468  //first, get ModelIDs corresponding to editedDataID AND triple_stage && select latest one
1469  QStringList query;
1470  query << "get_modelDescsIDs" << triple_information[ "eID" ];
1471  db->query( query );
1472 
1473  qDebug() << "In loadModel() Query: " << query;
1474 
1475  int latest_update_time = 1e100;
1476  int mID=0;
1477 
1478  while ( db->next() )
1479  {
1480  QString description = db->value( 0 ).toString();
1481  int modelID = db->value( 1 ).toInt();
1482  //QString date = US_Util::toUTCDatetimeText( db->value( 3 ).toDateTime().toString( "yyyy/MM/dd HH:mm" ), true );
1483  QDateTime date = db->value( 2 ).toDateTime();
1484 
1485  QDateTime now = QDateTime::currentDateTime();
1486 
1487  if ( description.contains( triple_information[ "stage_name" ] ) )
1488  {
1489  if ( triple_information[ "stage_name" ] == "2DSA" )
1490  {
1491  if ( !description.contains("-FM_") && !description.contains("-IT_") && !description.contains("-MC_") && !description.contains("_mcN") )
1492  {
1493  int time_to_now = date.secsTo(now);
1494  if ( time_to_now < latest_update_time )
1495  {
1496  latest_update_time = time_to_now;
1497  //qDebug() << "Edited profile MAX, NOW, DATE, sec-to-now -- " << latest_update_time << now << date << date.secsTo(now);
1498 
1499  qDebug() << "Model 2DSA: ID, desc, timetonow -- " << modelID << description << time_to_now;
1500 
1501  mID = modelID;
1502  }
1503  }
1504  }
1505  else
1506  {
1507  int time_to_now = date.secsTo(now);
1508  if ( time_to_now < latest_update_time )
1509  {
1510  latest_update_time = time_to_now;
1511  //qDebug() << "Edited profile MAX, NOW, DATE, sec-to-now -- " << latest_update_time << now << date << date.secsTo(now);
1512 
1513  qDebug() << "Model NON-2DSA: ID, desc, timetonow -- " << modelID << description << time_to_now;
1514 
1515  mID = modelID;
1516  }
1517  }
1518  }
1519  }
1520 
1521  int rc = 0;
1522  qDebug() << "ModelID to retrieve: -- " << mID;
1523  rc = model.load( QString::number( mID ), db );
1524  qDebug() << "LdM: model load rc" << rc;
1525  qApp->processEvents();
1526 
1527  model_loaded = model; // Save model exactly as loaded
1528  model_used = model; // Make that the working model
1529  is_dmga_mc = ( model.monteCarlo &&
1530  model.description.contains( "DMGA" ) &&
1531  model.description.contains( "_mcN" ) );
1532  qDebug() << "post-Load mC" << model.monteCarlo << "is_dmga_mc" << is_dmga_mc
1533  << "description" << model.description;
1534 
1535  if ( model.components.size() == 0 )
1536  {
1537  QMessageBox::critical( this, tr( "Empty Model" ),
1538  tr( "Loaded model has ZERO components!" ) );
1539  return false;
1540  }
1541 
1542  ti_noise.count = 0;
1543  ri_noise.count = 0;
1544  ti_noise.values.clear();
1545  ri_noise.values.clear();
1546 
1547  //Load noise files
1548  triple_information[ "mID" ] = QString::number( mID );
1549 
1550  progress_msg->setValue( 4 );
1551  qApp->processEvents();
1552 
1553  loadNoises( triple_information );
1554 
1555  return true;

1558 //Load Noises
1559 bool US_Analysis_auto::loadNoises( QMap < QString, QString > & triple_information )
1560 {
1561  US_Passwd pw;
1562  US_DB2* db = new US_DB2( pw.getPasswd() );
1563 
1564  if ( db->lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
1565  {
1566  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
1567  QMessageBox::information( this,
1568  tr( "DB Connection Problem" ),
1569  tr( "There was an error connecting to the database:\n" )
1570  + db->lastError() );
1571 
1572  return false;
1573  }
1574 
1575  // get noiseIDs, types & lastUpd by modelID
1576  QStringList query;
1577  query << "get_noiseTypesIDs" << triple_information[ "mID" ];
1578  db->query( query );
1579 
1580  qDebug() << "In loadNoises() Query: " << query;
1581 
1582  int latest_update_time_ti = 1e100;
1583  int latest_update_time_ri = 1e100;
1584  int nID_ti=0;
1585  int nID_ri=0;
1586 
1587  while ( db->next() )
1588  {
1589  int noiseID = db->value( 0 ).toInt();
1590  QString noiseType = db->value( 1 ).toString();
1591  //QString date = US_Util::toUTCDatetimeText( db->value( 2 ).toDateTime().toString( "yyyy/MM/dd HH:mm" ), true );
1592  QDateTime date = db->value( 2 ).toDateTime();
1593 
1594  QDateTime now = QDateTime::currentDateTime();
1595 
1596  qDebug() << "Noises: noiseID, noiseType, date -- " << noiseID << noiseType << date;
1597 
1598  if ( noiseType.contains( "ti_" ) )
1599  {
1600  int time_to_now = date.secsTo(now);
1601  if ( time_to_now < latest_update_time_ti )
1602  {
1603  latest_update_time_ti = time_to_now;
1604 
1605  nID_ti = noiseID;
1606  }
1607  }
1608  if ( noiseType.contains( "ri_" ) )
1609  {
1610  int time_to_now = date.secsTo(now);
1611  if ( time_to_now < latest_update_time_ri )
1612  {
1613  latest_update_time_ri = time_to_now;
1614 
1615  nID_ri = noiseID;
1616  }
1617  }
1618  }
1619 
1620 
1621  //ALEXEY: treat the case when model (like -MC does not possess its own noises -- use latest available noises for prior model like -IT )
1622  //int US_LoadableNoise::count_noise() in ../../gui/us_loadable_noise.cpp
1623  //void US_FeMatch::load_noise( ) in us_fematch.cpp
1624  if ( !nID_ti && !nID_ri )
1625  loadNoises_whenAbsent();
1626 
1627  //creare US_noise objects
1628  if ( nID_ti )
1629  {
1630  ti_noise.load( QString::number( nID_ti ), db );
1631  qDebug() << "loadNoises() NORMAL: ti_noise created: ID -- " << nID_ti;
1632  }
1633  if ( nID_ri )
1634  {
1635  ri_noise.load( QString::number( nID_ri ), db );
1636  qDebug() << "loadNoises() NORMAL: ri_noise created: ID -- " << nID_ri;
1637  }
1638 
1639  // noise loaded: insure that counts jive with data
1640  int ntinois = ti_noise.values.size();
1641  int nrinois = ri_noise.values.size();
1642  int nscans = edata->scanCount();
1643  int npoints = edata->pointCount();
1644  int npadded = 0;
1645 
1646 
1647  qDebug() << "ti_noise.count, ri_noise.count: " << ti_noise.count << ri_noise.count;
1648  qDebug() << "ti_noise.values.size(), ri_noise.values.size(): " << ti_noise.values.size() << ri_noise.values.size();
1649 
1650  if ( ntinois > 0 && ntinois < npoints )
1651  { // pad out ti noise values to radius count
1652  int jj = ntinois;
1653  while ( jj++ < npoints )
1654  ti_noise.values << 0.0;
1655  ti_noise.count = ti_noise.values.size();
1656  npadded++;
1657  }
1658 
1659  if ( nrinois > 0 && nrinois < nscans )
1660  { // pad out ri noise values to scan count
1661  int jj = nrinois;
1662  while ( jj++ < nscans )
1663  ri_noise.values << 0.0;
1664  ri_noise.count = ri_noise.values.size();
1665  npadded++;
1666  }
1667 
1668  if ( npadded > 0 )
1669  { // let user know that padding occurred
1670  QString pmsg;
1671 
1672  if ( npadded == 1 )
1673  pmsg = tr( "The noise file was padded out with zeroes\n"
1674  "in order to match the data range." );
1675  else
1676  pmsg = tr( "The noise files were padded out with zeroes\n"
1677  "in order to match the data ranges." );
1678 
1679  QMessageBox::information( this, tr( "Noise Padded Out" ), pmsg );
1680  }
1681 
1682  return true;
1683 }
1684 
1685 //Load Noises when absent for the model loaded (like -MC models)
1686 void US_Analysis_auto::loadNoises_whenAbsent( )
1687 {
1688  QStringList mieGUIDs; // list of GUIDs of models-in-edit
1689  QStringList nieGUIDs; // list of GUIDS:type:index of noises-in-edit
1690  QString editGUID = edata->editGUID; // loaded edit GUID
1691  QString modelGUID = model.modelGUID; // loaded model GUID
1692 
1693  int noisdf = US_Settings::noise_dialog();
1694  int nenois = count_noise_auto( edata, &model, mieGUIDs, nieGUIDs );
1695 
1696  qDebug() << "load_noise_whenAbsent(): mieGUIDs, nieGUIDs, editGUID, modelGUID -- " << mieGUIDs << nieGUIDs << editGUID << modelGUID;
1697  qDebug() << "load_noise_whenAbsent(): noisdf, nenois -- " << noisdf << nenois;
1698 
1699  if ( nenois > 0 )
1700  { // There is/are noise(s): ask user if she wants to load
1701  US_Passwd pw;
1702  US_DB2* dbP = new US_DB2( pw.getPasswd() );
1703 
1704  if ( nenois > 1 && noisdf == 0 )
1705  { // Noise exists and noise-dialog flag set to "Auto-load"
1706  QString descn = nieGUIDs.at( 0 );
1707  QString noiID = descn.section( ":", 0, 0 );
1708  QString typen = descn.section( ":", 1, 1 );
1709  QString mdlx1 = descn.section( ":", 2, 2 );
1710 
1711  if ( typen == "ti" )
1712  {
1713  ti_noise.load( true, noiID, dbP );
1714  qDebug() << "load_noise_whenAbsent(): ti_noise created: ID -- " << noiID;
1715  qDebug() << "load_noise_whenAbsent(): ti_noise.count: -- " << ti_noise.count;
1716  }
1717  else
1718  {
1719  ri_noise.load( true, noiID, dbP );
1720  qDebug() << "load_noise_whenAbsent(): ri_noise created: ID -- " << noiID;
1721  qDebug() << "load_noise_whenAbsent(): ri_noise.count: -- " << ri_noise.count;
1722  }
1723 
1724  descn = nieGUIDs.at( 1 );
1725  QString mdlx2 = descn.section( ":", 2, 2 );
1726  int kenois = ( mdlx1 == mdlx2 ) ? 2 : 1;
1727  if ( kenois == 2 )
1728  { // Second noise from same model: g/et it, too
1729  noiID = descn.section( ":", 0, 0 );
1730  typen = descn.section( ":", 1, 1 );
1731  if ( typen == "ti" )
1732  {
1733  ti_noise.load( true, noiID, dbP );
1734  qDebug() << "load_noise_whenAbsent(): Noise 2: noiID, loaded ti--" << noiID;
1735  qDebug() << "load_noise_whenAbsent(): Noise 2: noiID, loaded ti_noise.count --" << ti_noise.count;
1736  }
1737  else
1738  {
1739  ri_noise.load( true, noiID, dbP );
1740  qDebug() << "load_noise_whenAbsent(): Noise 2: noiID, loaded ri--" << noiID;
1741  qDebug() << "load_noise_whenAbsent(): Noise 2: noiID, loaded ri_noise.count --" << ri_noise.count;
1742  }
1743  }
1744 
1745  }
1746  else
1747  { // only 1: just load it
1748  QString noiID = nieGUIDs.at( 0 );
1749  QString typen = noiID.section( ":", 1, 1 );
1750  noiID = noiID.section( ":", 0, 0 );
1751 
1752  if ( typen == "ti" )
1753  ti_noise.load( true, noiID, dbP );
1754 
1755  else
1756  ri_noise.load( true, noiID, dbP );
1757  }
1758 
1759  }
1760 
1761 
1762 }

1765 // Determine if edit/model related noise available and build lists
1766 int US_Analysis_auto::count_noise_auto( US_DataIO::EditedData* edata,
1767  US_Model* model, QStringList& mieGUIDs, QStringList& nieGUIDs )
1768 {
1769  int noidiag = US_Settings::noise_dialog();
1770 
1771  int nenois = 0; // number of edited-data-related noises
1772 
1773  if ( edata == NULL )
1774  return nenois;
1775 
1776  QStringList nimGUIDs; // list of GUIDs:type:index of noises-in-models
1777  QStringList tmpGUIDs; // temporary noises-in-model list
1778  QString daEditGUID = edata->editGUID; // loaded edit GUID
1779  QString modelGUID = ( model == 0 ) ? // loaded model GUID
1780  "" : model->modelGUID;
1781  QString lmodlGUID; // list model GUID
1782  QString lnoisGUID; // list noise GUID
1783  QString modelIndx; // "0001" style model index
1784 
1785  id_list_db_auto ( daEditGUID );
1786 
1787  // Get a list of models-with-noise tied to the loaded edit
1788  int nemods = models_in_edit_auto ( daEditGUID, mieGUIDs );
1789 
1790  if ( nemods == 0 )
1791  {
1792  //QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
1793  return nemods; // Go no further if no models-with-noise for edit
1794  }
1795 
1796  int latemx = 0; // Index to latest model-in-edit
1797 
1798  // If no model is loaded, pick the model GUID of the latest noise
1799  if ( model == 0 )
1800  modelGUID = mieGUIDs[ latemx ];
1801 
1802  // Get a list of noises tied to the loaded model
1803  int nmnois = noises_in_model_auto( modelGUID, nimGUIDs );
1804 
1805  // If the loaded model has no noise, try the latest model
1806  if ( nmnois == 0 )
1807  {
1808  modelGUID = mieGUIDs[ latemx ];
1809  nmnois = noises_in_model_auto( modelGUID, nimGUIDs );
1810  }
1811 
1812  // Insure that the loaded/latest model heads the model-in-edit list
1813  if ( modelGUID != mieGUIDs[ 0 ] )
1814  {
1815  if ( ! mieGUIDs.removeOne( modelGUID ) )
1816  {
1817  qDebug( "*ERROR* Loaded/Latest model not in model-in-edit list!" );
1818  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
1819  return 0;
1820  }
1821 
1822  mieGUIDs.insert( 0, modelGUID );
1823  }
1824 
1825 
1826  int kk = 0; // running output models index
1827 
1828  if ( nmnois > 0 )
1829  { // If loaded model has noise, put noise in list
1830  nieGUIDs << nimGUIDs; // initialize noise-in-edit list
1831  kk++;
1832  }
1833 
1834  nenois = nmnois; // initial noise-in-edit count is noises in model
1835 
1836  for ( int ii = 1; ii < nemods; ii++ )
1837  { // Search through models in edit
1838  lmodlGUID = mieGUIDs[ ii ]; // this model's GUID
1839  modelIndx = QString().sprintf( "%4.4d", kk ); // models-in-edit index
1840 
1841  // Find the noises tied to this model
1842  int kenois = noises_in_model_auto( lmodlGUID, tmpGUIDs );
1843 
1844  if ( kenois > 0 )
1845  { // if we have 1 or 2 noises, add to noise-in-edit list
1846  nenois += qMin( 2, kenois );
1847  // adjust entry to have the right model-in-edit index
1848  lnoisGUID = tmpGUIDs.at( 0 ).section( ":", 0, 1 )
1849  + ":" + modelIndx;
1850  nieGUIDs << lnoisGUID;
1851  if ( kenois > 1 )
1852  { // add a second noise to the list
1853  lnoisGUID = tmpGUIDs.at( 1 ).section( ":", 0, 1 )
1854  + ":" + modelIndx;
1855  nieGUIDs << lnoisGUID;
1856  }
1857 
1858  kk++;
1859  }
1860  }
1861 
1862 
1863  if ( nenois > 0 )
1864  { // There is/are noise(s): ask user if she wants to load
1865  QMessageBox msgBox;
1866  QString amsg;
1867  QString msg;
1868 
1869  if ( model == 0 )
1870  amsg = tr( ", associated with the loaded edit.\n" );
1871 
1872  else
1873  amsg = tr( ", associated with the loaded edit/model.\n" );
1874 
1875  if ( nenois > 1 )
1876  {
1877  msg = tr( "There are noise files" ) + amsg
1878  + tr( "Do you want to load some of them?" );
1879  }
1880 
1881  else
1882  { // Single noise file: check its value range versus experiment
1883  QString noiID = nieGUIDs.at( 0 ).section( ":", 0, 0 );
1884  US_Noise i_noise;
1885 
1886  US_Passwd pw;
1887  US_DB2 db( pw.getPasswd() );
1888  i_noise.load( true, noiID, &db );
1889 
1890  double datmin = edata->value( 0, 0 );
1891  double datmax = datmin;
1892  double noimin = 1.0e10;
1893  double noimax = -noimin;
1894  int npoint = edata->pointCount();
1895 
1896  for ( int ii = 0; ii < edata->scanData.size(); ii++ )
1897  {
1898  for ( int jj = 0; jj < npoint; jj++ )
1899  {
1900  double datval = edata->value( ii, jj );
1901  datmin = qMin( datmin, datval );
1902  datmax = qMax( datmax, datval );
1903  }
1904  }
1905 
1906  for ( int ii = 0; ii < i_noise.values.size(); ii++ )
1907  {
1908  double noival = i_noise.values[ ii ];
1909  noimin = qMin( noimin, noival );
1910  noimax = qMax( noimax, noival );
1911  }
1912 
1913  if ( ( noimax - noimin ) > ( datmax - datmin ) )
1914  { // Insert a warning if noise appears corrupt or unusual
1915  amsg = amsg
1916  + tr( "\nBUT THE NOISE HAS AN UNUSUALLY LARGE DATA RANGE.\n\n" );
1917  }
1918 
1919  msg = tr( "There is a noise file" ) + amsg
1920  + tr( "Do you want to load it?" );
1921  }
1922 
1923 DbgLv(2) << "LaNoi:noidiag " << noidiag;
1924  if ( noidiag > 0 )
1925  {
1926  msgBox.setWindowTitle( tr( "Edit/Model Associated Noise" ) );
1927  msgBox.setText( msg );
1928  msgBox.setStandardButtons( QMessageBox::No | QMessageBox::Yes );
1929  msgBox.setDefaultButton( QMessageBox::Yes );
1930 
1931  if ( msgBox.exec() != QMessageBox::Yes )
1932  { // user did not say "yes": return zero count
1933  nenois = 0; // number of edited-data-related noises
1934  }
1935  }
1936 
1937  if ( kk < nemods )
1938  { // Models with noise were found, so truncate models list
1939  for ( int ii = 0; ii < ( nemods - kk ); ii++ )
1940  mieGUIDs.removeLast();
1941  }
1942  }
1943 
1944  return nenois;
1945 }

1948 // build a list of noise(GUIDs) for a given model(GUID)
1949 int US_Analysis_auto::noises_in_model_auto( QString mGUID, QStringList& nGUIDs )
1950 {
1951  QString xnGUID;
1952  QString xmGUID;
1953  QString xntype;
1954 
1955  nGUIDs.clear();
1956 
1957  for ( int ii = 0; ii < noiIDs.size(); ii++ )
1958  { // Examine noises list; Save to this list if model GUID matches
1959  xnGUID = noiIDs .at( ii );
1960  xmGUID = noiMoIDs.at( ii );
1961  xntype = noiTypes.at( ii );
1962 
1963  xntype = xntype.contains( "ri_nois", Qt::CaseInsensitive ) ?
1964  "ri" : "ti";
1965 
1966  if ( mGUID == xmGUID )
1967  nGUIDs << xnGUID + ":" + xntype + ":0000";
1968  }
1969 
1970  return nGUIDs.size();
1971 }

1973 // Build a list of models(GUIDs) for a given edit(GUID)
1974 int US_Analysis_auto::models_in_edit_auto( QString eGUID, QStringList& mGUIDs )
1975 {
1976  QString xmGUID;
1977  QString xeGUID;
1978  QString xrGUID;
1979  QStringList reGUIDs;
1980 
1981  mGUIDs.clear();
1982 
1983  for ( int ii = 0; ii < modIDs.size(); ii++ )
1984  { // Examine models list; Save to this list if edit GUID matches
1985  xmGUID = modIDs.at( ii );
1986  xeGUID = modEdIDs.at( ii );
1987 
1988  if ( eGUID == xeGUID )
1989  {
1990  mGUIDs << xmGUID;
1991  }
1992  }
1993 
1994  return mGUIDs.size();
1995 }

1997 // Build lists of noise and model IDs for database
1998 int US_Analysis_auto::id_list_db_auto( QString daEditGUID )
1999 {
2000  QStringList query;
2001 
2002  US_Passwd pw;
2003  US_DB2 db( pw.getPasswd() );
2004 
2005  if ( db.lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
2006  return 0;
2007 
2008  query.clear();
2009  query << "get_editID" << daEditGUID;
2010  db.query( query );
2011  db.next();
2012  QString daEditID = db.value( 0 ).toString();
2013 DbgLv(1) << "LaNoi:idlDB: daEdit ID GUID" << daEditID << daEditGUID;
2014 
2015  noiIDs .clear();
2016  noiEdIDs.clear();
2017  noiMoIDs.clear();
2018  noiTypes.clear();
2019  modIDs .clear();
2020  modEdIDs.clear();
2021  modDescs.clear();
2022 
2023  QStringList reqIDs;
2024  QString noiEdID;
2025 
2026  // Build noise, edit, model ID lists for all noises
2027  query.clear();
2028  query << "get_noise_desc_by_editID" << QString::number( invID ) << daEditID;
2029  db.query( query );
2030 
2031  while ( db.next() )
2032  { // Accumulate lists from noise records
2033  noiEdID = db.value( 2 ).toString();
2034 
2035  noiIDs << db.value( 1 ).toString();
2036  noiTypes << db.value( 4 ).toString();
2037  noiMoIDs << db.value( 5 ).toString();
2038  }
2039 
2040 DbgLv(1) << "LaNoi:idlDB: noiTypes size" << noiTypes.size();
2041  // Build model, edit ID lists for all models
2042  query.clear();
2043  query << "get_model_desc_by_editID" << QString::number( invID ) << daEditID;
2044  db.query( query );
2045 
2046  while ( db.next() )
2047  { // Accumulate from db desc entries matching noise model IDs
2048  QString modGUID = db.value( 1 ).toString();
2049  QString modEdID = db.value( 6 ).toString();
2050 
2051  if ( noiMoIDs.contains( modGUID ) && modEdID == daEditID )
2052  { // Only list models that have associated noise and match edit
2053  modIDs << modGUID;
2054  modDescs << db.value( 2 ).toString();
2055  modEdIDs << db.value( 5 ).toString();
2056  }
2057  }
2058 DbgLv(1) << "LaNoi:idlDB: modDescs size" << modDescs.size();
2059 
2060  // Loop through models to edit out any extra monteCarlo models
2061  for ( int ii = modIDs.size() - 1; ii >=0; ii-- )
2062  { // Work from the back so any removed records do not affect indexes
2063  QString mdesc = modDescs.at( ii );
2064  QString asysID = mdesc.section( ".", -2, -2 );
2065  bool mCarlo = ( asysID.contains( "-MC" ) &&
2066  asysID.contains( "_mc" ) );
2067  QString reqID = asysID.section( "_", 0, -2 );
2068 
2069  if ( mCarlo )
2070  { // Treat monte carlo in a special way (as single composite model)
2071  if ( reqIDs.contains( reqID ) )
2072  { // already have this request GUID, so remove this model
2073  modIDs .removeAt( ii );
2074  modDescs.removeAt( ii );
2075  modEdIDs.removeAt( ii );
2076  }
2077 
2078  else
2079  { // This is the first time for this request, so save it in a list
2080  reqIDs << reqID;
2081  }
2082  }
2083  }
2084 
2085  // Create list of edit GUIDs for noises
2086  for ( int ii = 0; ii < noiTypes.size(); ii++ )
2087  {
2088  QString moGUID = noiMoIDs.at( ii );
2089  int jj = modIDs.indexOf( moGUID );
2090 DbgLv(2) << "LaNoi:idlDB: ii jj moGUID" << ii << jj << moGUID;
2091 
2092  QString edGUID = ( jj < 0 ) ? "" : modEdIDs.at( jj );
2093 
2094  noiEdIDs << edGUID;
2095  }
2096 
2097  return noiIDs.size();
2098 }

2101 //Simulate Model
2102 void US_Analysis_auto::simulateModel( )
2103 {
2104  progress_msg->setLabelText( "Simulating model..." );
2105  progress_msg->setValue( 0 );
2106 
2107  int nconc = edata->pointCount();
2108  double radlo = edata->radius( 0 );
2109  double radhi = edata->radius( nconc - 1 );
2110 
2111  int lc=model_used.components.size()-1;
2112  qDebug() << "SimMdl: 0) s D c"
2113  << model_used.components[ 0].s << model_used.components[ 0].D
2114  << model_used.components[ 0].signal_concentration << " n" << lc;
2115  qDebug() << "SimMdl: n) s D c"
2116  << model_used.components[lc].s << model_used.components[lc].D
2117  << model_used.components[lc].signal_concentration;
2118 
2119  adjustModel();
2120 
2121  qDebug() << "SimMdl: 0) s D c"
2122  << model.components[ 0].s << model.components[ 0].D
2123  << model.components[ 0].signal_concentration;
2124  qDebug() << "SimMdl: n) s D c"
2125  << model.components[lc].s << model.components[lc].D
2126  << model.components[lc].signal_concentration;
2127 
2128  // Initialize simulation parameters using edited data information
2129  US_Passwd pw;
2130  US_DB2* dbP = new US_DB2( pw.getPasswd() );
2131 
2132  simparams.initFromData( dbP, *edata, dat_steps );
2133  simparams.simpoints = adv_vals[ "simpoints" ].toInt();
2134  simparams.meshType = US_SimulationParameters::ASTFEM;
2135  simparams.gridType = US_SimulationParameters::MOVING;
2136  simparams.radial_resolution = (double)( radhi - radlo ) / ( nconc - 1 );
2137  // simparams.bottom = simparams.bottom_position;
2138  qDebug() << "SimMdl: simpoints" << simparams.simpoints
2139  << "rreso" << simparams.radial_resolution
2140  << "bottom_sim" << simparams.bottom << "bottom_dat" << edata->bottom;
2141  //simparams.meniscus = 5.8;
2142 
2143  //sdata.scanData.resize( total_scans );
2144  //int terpsize = ( points + 7 ) / 8;
2145 
2146  if ( exp_steps )
2147  simparams.speed_step = speed_steps;
2148 
2149  qDebug() << "SimMdl: speed_steps:" << simparams.speed_step.size();
2150 
2151  QString mtyp = adv_vals[ "meshtype" ];
2152  QString gtyp = adv_vals[ "gridtype" ];
2153  QString bvol = adv_vals[ "bandvolume" ];
2154 
2155 
2156  if ( gtyp.contains( "Constant" ) )
2157  simparams.gridType = US_SimulationParameters::FIXED;
2158 
2159  if ( model.components[ 0 ].sigma == 0.0 &&
2160  model.components[ 0 ].delta == 0.0)
2161  simparams.meshType = US_SimulationParameters::ASTFEM;
2162  else
2163  simparams.meshType = US_SimulationParameters::ASTFVM;
2164 
2165  simparams.firstScanIsConcentration = false;
2166 
2167  double concval1 = 0.0;
2168 
2169  if ( simparams.band_forming )
2170  {
2171  simparams.band_volume = bvol.toDouble();
2172  //concval1 = 1.0;
2173  //simparams.firstScanIsConcentration = true;
2174  }
2175  else
2176  simparams.band_volume = 0.0;
2177 
2178  // Make a simulation copy of the experimental data without actual readings
2179 
2180  qDebug() << "SimulateModel: --- 1";
2181 
2182  US_AstfemMath::initSimData( *sdata, *edata, concval1 );// Gets experimental time grid set
2183 
2184  qDebug() << "SimulateModel: --- 2";
2185 
2186 
2187  QString tmst_fpath = US_Settings::resultDir() + "/" + FileName_parsed + "/"
2188  + FileName_parsed + ".time_state.tmst";
2189  QFileInfo check_file( tmst_fpath );
2190  simparams.sim = ( edata->channel == "S" );
2191 
2192  if ( ( check_file.exists() ) && ( check_file.isFile() ) )
2193  {
2194  if ( US_AstfemMath::timestate_onesec( tmst_fpath, *sdata ) )
2195  { // Load timestate that is already at 1-second-intervals
2196  simparams.simSpeedsFromTimeState( tmst_fpath );
2197  qDebug() << "SimMdl: timestate file exists" << tmst_fpath << " timestateobject,count = "
2198  << simparams.tsobj << simparams.sim_speed_prof.count();
2199  simparams.speedstepsFromSSprof();
2200  }
2201 
2202  else
2203  { // Replace timestate with a new one that is at 1-second-intervals
2204  // if ( drow == 0 )
2205  // {
2206  QString tmst_fdefs = QString( tmst_fpath ).replace( ".tmst", ".xml" );
2207  QString tmst_fpsav = tmst_fpath + "-orig";
2208  QString tmst_fdsav = tmst_fdefs + "-orig";
2209  simparams.sim = ( edata->channel == "S" );
2210 
2211  // Rename existing (non-1sec-intv) files
2212  QFile::rename( tmst_fpath, tmst_fpsav );
2213  QFile::rename( tmst_fdefs, tmst_fdsav );
2214  // Create a new 1-second-interval file set
2215  US_AstfemMath::writetimestate( tmst_fpath, simparams, *sdata );
2216  qDebug() << "SimMdl: 1-sec-intv file created";
2217  // }
2218 
2219  simparams.simSpeedsFromTimeState( tmst_fpath );
2220  simparams.speedstepsFromSSprof();
2221  }
2222  }
2223  else
2224  {
2225  qDebug() << "SimMdl: timestate file does not exist";
2226  if ( ! simparams.sim )
2227  { // Compute acceleration rate for non-astfem_sim data
2228  const double tfac = ( 4.0 / 3.0 );
2229  double t2 = simparams.speed_step[ 0 ].time_first;
2230  double w2t = simparams.speed_step[ 0 ].w2t_first;
2231  double om1t = simparams.speed_step[ 0 ].rotorspeed * M_PI / 30.0;
2232  double w2 = sq( om1t );
2233  double t1 = tfac * ( t2 - ( w2t / w2 ) );
2234  int t_acc = (int)qRound( t1 );
2235  double rate = (double)( simparams.speed_step[ 0 ].rotorspeed )
2236  / (double)t_acc;
2237  qDebug() << "SimMdl: accel-calc: t1 t2 w2t t_acc speed rate"
2238  << t1 << t2 << w2t << t_acc << simparams.speed_step[0].rotorspeed << rate;
2239  simparams.speed_step[ 0 ].acceleration = (int)qRound( rate );
2240  }
2241  }
2242 
2243  // Do a quick test of the speed step implied by TimeState
2244  int tf_scan = simparams.speed_step[ 0 ].time_first;
2245  int accel1 = simparams.speed_step[ 0 ].acceleration;
2246  QString svalu = US_Settings::debug_value( "SetSpeedLowA" );
2247  int lo_ss_acc = svalu.isEmpty() ? 250 : svalu.toInt();
2248  int rspeed = simparams.speed_step[ 0 ].rotorspeed;
2249  double tf_aend = static_cast<double>(tf_scan);
2250  // prevent any division by zero
2251  if (accel1 != 0)
2252  {
2253  tf_aend = static_cast<double>(rspeed) / static_cast<double>(accel1);
2254  }
2255 
2256  qDebug() << "SimMdl: ssck: rspeed accel1 lo_ss_acc"
2257  << rspeed << accel1 << lo_ss_acc << "tf_aend tf_scan"
2258  << tf_aend << tf_scan;
2259  //x0 1 2 3 4 5
2260  // check if the acceleration rate is low or the first scan was taken before the acceleration ended
2261  // Due to older, wrong timestate calculation there might be a case, in which the calculated end of acceleration can
2262  // be up to 1 second later than expected, tf_scan + 1 accounts for this.
2263  if ( accel1 < lo_ss_acc || tf_aend > ( tf_scan + 1 ) )
2264  {
2265  QString wmsg = tr( "The TimeState computed/used is likely bad:<br/>"
2266  "The acceleration implied is %1 rpm/sec.<br/>"
2267  "The acceleration zone ends at %2 seconds,<br/>"
2268  "with a first scan time of %3 seconds.<br/><br/>"
2269  "<b>You should rerun the experiment without<br/>"
2270  "any interim constant speed, and then<br/>"
2271  "you should reimport the data.</b>" )
2272  .arg( accel1 ).arg( QString::number(tf_aend) ).arg( QString::number(tf_scan) );
2273 
2274  QMessageBox msgBox( this );
2275  msgBox.setWindowTitle( tr( "Bad TimeState Implied!" ) );
2276  msgBox.setTextFormat( Qt::RichText );
2277  msgBox.setText( wmsg );
2278  msgBox.addButton( tr( "Continue" ), QMessageBox::RejectRole );
2279  QPushButton* bAbort = msgBox.addButton( tr( "Abort" ),
2280  QMessageBox::YesRole );
2281  msgBox.setDefaultButton( bAbort );
2282  msgBox.exec();
2283  if ( msgBox.clickedButton() == bAbort )
2284  {
2285  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
2286  qApp->processEvents();
2287  return;
2288  }
2289  }
2290  sdata->cell = rdata->cell;
2291  sdata->channel = rdata->channel;
2292  sdata->description = rdata->description;
2293 
2294  if ( dbg_level > 0 )
2295  simparams.save_simparms( US_Settings::etcDir() + "/sp_fematch.xml" );
2296 
2297  //start_time = QDateTime::currentDateTime();
2298  int ncomp = model.components.size();
2299  //compress = le_compress->text().toDouble();
2300  progress_msg->setRange( 1, ncomp );
2301  // progress_msg->reset();
2302 
2303  nthread = US_Settings::threads();
2304  int ntc = ( ncomp + nthread - 1 ) / nthread;
2305  nthread = ( ntc > MIN_NTC ) ? nthread : 1;
2306 
2307  /*
2308  //TEST
2309  nthread = 10;
2310  */
2311 
2312  qDebug() << "SimMdl: nthread" << nthread << "ncomp" << ncomp
2313  << "ntc" << ntc << "meshtype" << simparams.meshType;
2314 
2315  // Do simulation by several possible ways: 1-/Multi-thread, ASTFEM/ASTFVM
2316  if ( nthread < 2 )
2317  {
2318  if ( model.components[ 0 ].sigma == 0.0 &&
2319  model.components[ 0 ].delta == 0.0 &&
2320  model.coSedSolute < 0.0 &&
2321  compress == 0.0 )
2322  {
2323  qDebug() << "SimMdl: (fematch:)Finite Element Solver is called";
2324  //*DEBUG*
2325  for(int ii=0; ii<model.components.size(); ii++ )
2326  {
2327  qDebug() << "SimMdl: comp" << ii << "s D v"
2328  << model.components[ii].s
2329  << model.components[ii].D
2330  << model.components[ii].vbar20 << " c"
2331  << model.components[ii].signal_concentration;
2332  }
2333  qDebug() << "SimMdl: (fematch:)Sim Pars--";
2334  simparams.debug();
2335  //*DEBUG*
2336  US_Astfem_RSA* astfem_rsa = new US_Astfem_RSA( model, simparams );
2337 
2338  connect( astfem_rsa, SIGNAL( current_component( int ) ),
2339  this, SLOT ( update_progress ( int ) ) );
2340  astfem_rsa->set_debug_flag( dbg_level );
2341  solution_rec.buffer.compressibility = compress;
2342  solution_rec.buffer.manual = manual;
2343  //astfem_rsa->set_buffer( solution_rec.buffer );
2344 
2345  astfem_rsa->calculate( *sdata );
2346  //*DEBUG*
2347  int kpts=0;
2348  double trmsd=0.0;
2349  double tnoi=0.0;
2350  double rnoi=0.0;
2351  bool ftin=ti_noise.count > 0;
2352  bool frin=ri_noise.count > 0;
2353  for(int ss=0; ss<sdata->scanCount(); ss++)
2354  {
2355  rnoi = frin ? ri_noise.values[ss] : 0.0;
2356  for (int rr=0; rr<sdata->pointCount(); rr++)
2357  {
2358  tnoi = ftin ? ti_noise.values[rr] : 0.0;
2359  double rval=edata->value(ss,rr) - sdata->value(ss,rr) - rnoi - tnoi;
2360  trmsd += sq( rval );
2361  kpts++;
2362  }
2363  }
2364  trmsd = sqrt( trmsd / (float)kpts );
2365  qDebug() << "SimMdl: (1)trmsd" << trmsd;
2366  //*DEBUG*
2367  }
2368  else
2369  {
2370  qDebug() << "SimMdl: (fematch:)Finite Volume Solver is called";
2371  US_LammAstfvm *astfvm = new US_LammAstfvm( model, simparams );
2372  astfvm->calculate( *sdata );
2373  }
2374  //-----------------------
2375  //Simulation part is over
2376  //-----------------------
2377 
2378  show_results();
2379  }
2380 
2381  else
2382  { // Do multi-thread calculations
2383 
2384  qDebug() << "Simulate Model: Multi-thread -- ";
2385 
2386  solution_rec.buffer.compressibility = compress;
2387  solution_rec.buffer.manual = manual;
2388  tsimdats.clear();
2389  tmodels .clear();
2390  kcomps .clear();
2391  QList< ThreadWorker* > tworkers;
2392  QList< QThreadEx* > wthreads;
2393 
2394  // Build models for each thread
2395  for ( int ii = 0; ii < ncomp; ii++ )
2396  {
2397  if ( ii < nthread )
2398  { // First time through per thread: get initial model and sim data
2399  tmodels << model;
2400  tmodels[ ii ].components.clear();
2401  US_DataIO::RawData sdat = *sdata;
2402  tsimdats << sdat;
2403  kcomps << 0;
2404  }
2405 
2406  // Partition thread models from round-robin fetch of components
2407  int jj = ii % nthread;
2408  tmodels[ jj ].components << model.components[ ii ];
2409  }
2410 
2411  thrdone = 0;
2412  solution_rec.buffer.manual = manual;
2413 
2414  // Build worker threads and begin running
2415  for ( int ii = 0; ii < nthread; ii++ )
2416  {
2417  ThreadWorker* tworker = new ThreadWorker( tmodels[ ii ], simparams,
2418  tsimdats[ ii ], solution_rec.buffer, ii );
2419  QThreadEx* wthread = new QThreadEx();
2420 
2421  tworker->moveToThread( wthread );
2422 
2423  tworkers << tworker;
2424  wthreads << wthread;
2425 
2426  connect( wthread, SIGNAL( started() ),
2427  tworker, SLOT ( calc_simulation() ) );
2428 
2429  connect( tworker, SIGNAL( work_progress ( int, int ) ),
2430  this, SLOT( thread_progress( int, int ) ) );
2431  connect( tworker, SIGNAL( work_complete ( int ) ),
2432  this, SLOT( thread_complete( int ) ) );
2433 
2434  wthread->start();
2435  }
2436  }
2437 
2438 }

2491 // Calculate residual absorbance values (data - sim - noise)
2492 void US_Analysis_auto::calc_residuals()
2493 {
2494  int dsize = edata->pointCount();
2495  int ssize = sdata->pointCount();
2496  QVector< double > vecxx( dsize );
2497  QVector< double > vecsx( ssize );
2498  QVector< double > vecsy( ssize );
2499  double* xx = vecxx.data();
2500  double* sx = vecsx.data();
2501  double* sy = vecsy.data();
2502  double yval;
2503  double sval;
2504  double rmsd = 0.0;
2505  double tnoi = 0.0;
2506  double rnoi = 0.0;
2507  bool ftin = ti_noise.count > 0;
2508  bool frin = ri_noise.count > 0;
2509  bool matchd = ( dsize == ssize );
2510  int kpts = 0;
2511  qDebug() << "CALC_RESID: matchd" << matchd << "dsize ssize" << dsize << ssize;
2512  int kexcls=0;
2513 
2514  QVector< double > resscan;
2515 
2516  resids .clear();
2517  resscan.resize( dsize );
2518 
2519  for ( int jj = 0; jj < dsize; jj++ )
2520  {
2521  xx[ jj ] = edata->radius( jj );
2522  }
2523 
2524  for ( int jj = 0; jj < ssize; jj++ )
2525  {
2526  sx[ jj ] = sdata->radius( jj );
2527  if ( sx[ jj ] != xx[ jj ] ) matchd = false;
2528  }
2529 
2530  for ( int ii = 0; ii < scanCount; ii++ )
2531  {
2532  bool usescan = !excludedScans.contains( ii );
2533 if(!usescan) kexcls++;
2534 
2535  rnoi = frin ? ri_noise.values[ ii ] : 0.0;
2536 
2537  for ( int jj = 0; jj < ssize; jj++ )
2538  {
2539  sy[ jj ] = sdata->value( ii, jj );
2540  }
2541 
2542  for ( int jj = 0; jj < dsize; jj++ )
2543  { // Calculate the residuals and the RMSD
2544  tnoi = ftin ? ti_noise.values[ jj ] : 0.0;
2545 
2546  if ( matchd )
2547  sval = sy[ jj ];
2548  else
2549  sval = interp_sval( xx[ jj ], sx, sy, ssize );
2550 
2551  yval = edata->value( ii, jj ) - sval - rnoi - tnoi;
2552 
2553  if ( usescan )
2554  {
2555  rmsd += sq( yval );
2556  kpts++;
2557  }
2558 
2559  resscan[ jj ] = yval;
2560  }
2561 
2562  resids << resscan;
2563  }
2564 
2565  rmsd /= (double)( kpts );
2566  //le_variance->setText( QString::number( rmsd ) );
2567  rmsd = sqrt( rmsd );
2568  //le_rmsd ->setText( QString::number( rmsd ) );
2569  qDebug() << "CALC_RESID: matchd" << matchd << "kexcls" << kexcls << "rmsd" << rmsd;
2570 }
2571 
2572 // Interpolate an sdata y (readings) value for a given x (radius)
2573 double US_Analysis_auto::interp_sval( double xv, double* sx, double* sy, int ssize )
2574 {
2575  for ( int jj = 1; jj < ssize; jj++ )
2576  {
2577  if ( xv == sx[ jj ] )
2578  {
2579  return sy[ jj ];
2580  }
2581 
2582  if ( xv < sx[ jj ] )
2583  { // given x lower than array x: interpolate between point and previous
2584  int ii = jj - 1;
2585  double dx = sx[ jj ] - sx[ ii ];
2586  double dy = sy[ jj ] - sy[ ii ];
2587  return ( sy[ ii ] + ( xv - sx[ ii ] ) * dy / dx );
2588  }
2589  }
2590 
2591  // given x position not found: interpolate using last two points
2592  int jj = ssize - 1;
2593  int ii = jj - 1;
2594  double dx = sx[ jj ] - sx[ ii ];
2595  double dy = sy[ jj ] - sy[ ii ];
2596  return ( sy[ ii ] + ( xv - sx[ ii ] ) * dy / dx );
2597 }

2638 // Update progress when thread reports
2639 void US_Analysis_auto::thread_progress( int thr, int icomp )
2640 {
2641  qDebug() << "Updating progress multiple threads, thr, icomp -- " << thr << icomp;
2642  int kcomp = 0;
2643  kcomps[ thr ] = icomp;
2644  for ( int ii = 0; ii < nthread; ii++ )
2645  kcomp += kcomps[ ii ];

2651 // Update count of threads completed and colate simulations when all are done
2652 void US_Analysis_auto::thread_complete( int thr )
2653 {
2654  thrdone++;
2655  qDebug() << "THR COMPL thr" << thr << "thrdone" << thrdone;
2656 
2657  if ( thrdone >= nthread )
2658  { // All threads are done, so sum thread simulation data
2659  for ( int ii = 0; ii < sdata->scanData.size(); ii++ )
2660  {
2661  for ( int jj = 0; jj < sdata->xvalues.size(); jj++ )
2662  {
2663  //double conc = 0.0;
2664  double conc = sdata->value( ii, jj );
2665 
2666  for ( int kk = 0; kk < nthread; kk++ )
2667  conc += tsimdats[ kk ].value( ii, jj );
2668 
2669  sdata->setValue( ii, jj, conc );
2670  }
2671  }
2672 
2673  // Then show the results
2674  show_results();
2675  }
2676 }

2678 // Adjust model components based on buffer, vbar, and temperature
2679 void US_Analysis_auto::adjustModel( )
2680 {
2681  model = model_used;
2682 
2683  // build model component correction factors
2684  double avgTemp = edata->average_temperature();
2685  double vbar20 = svbar_global.toDouble();
2686 
2687  solution.density = density;
2688  solution.viscosity = viscosity;
2689  solution.manual = manual;
2690  solution.vbar20 = vbar20;
2691  solution.vbar = US_Math2::calcCommonVbar( solution_rec, avgTemp );
2692 // solution.vbar = US_Math2::adjust_vbar20( solution.vbar20, avgTemp );
2693 
2694  US_Math2::data_correction( avgTemp, solution );
2695 
2696  double scorrec = solution.s20w_correction;
2697  double dcorrec = solution.D20w_correction;
2698  double mc_vbar = model.components[ 0 ].vbar20;
2699  // Set constant-vbar and constant-ff0 flags
2700  cnstvb = model.constant_vbar();
2701  cnstff = model.constant_ff0();
2702 
2703  US_Math2::SolutionData sd;
2704  sd.density = solution.density;
2705  sd.viscosity = solution.viscosity;
2706  sd.vbar20 = solution.vbar20;
2707  sd.vbar = solution.vbar;
2708  sd.manual = solution.manual;
2709  qDebug() << "Fem:Adj: avgT" << avgTemp << "scorr dcorr" << scorrec << dcorrec;
2710 
2711  if ( cnstvb && mc_vbar != sd.vbar20 && mc_vbar != 0.0 )
2712  { // Use vbar from the model component, instead of from the solution
2713  sd.vbar20 = mc_vbar;
2714  sd.vbar = US_Math2::adjust_vbar20( sd.vbar20, avgTemp );
2715  US_Math2::data_correction( avgTemp, sd );
2716  scorrec = sd.s20w_correction;
2717  dcorrec = sd.D20w_correction;
2718  qDebug() << "Fem:Adj: cnstvb" << cnstvb << " scorr dcorr" << scorrec << dcorrec;
2719  }
2720  qDebug() << "Fem:Adj: avgT" << avgTemp << "vb20 vb" << sd.vbar20 << sd.vbar;
2721 
2722  // Convert to experiment space: adjust s,D based on solution,temperature
2723 
2724  for ( int jj = 0; jj < model.components.size(); jj++ )
2725  {
2726  US_Model::SimulationComponent* sc = &model.components[ jj ];
2727 
2728  sc->vbar20 = ( sc->vbar20 == 0.0 ) ? vbar20 : sc->vbar20;
2729 
2730  if ( ! cnstvb )
2731  { // Set s,D corrections based on component vbar
2732  sd.vbar20 = sc->vbar20;
2733  sd.vbar = US_Math2::adjust_vbar20( sd.vbar20, avgTemp );
2734  US_Math2::data_correction( avgTemp, sd );
2735  scorrec = sd.s20w_correction;
2736  dcorrec = sd.D20w_correction;
2737  }
2738 
2739 double s20w=sc->s;
2740 double d20w=sc->D;
2741  sc->s /= scorrec;
2742  sc->D /= dcorrec;
2743  qDebug() << "Fem:Adj: s20w D20w" << s20w << d20w
2744  << "s D" << sc->s << sc->D << " jj" << jj << "vb20 vb" << sc->vbar20 << sd.vbar;
2745 
2746  if ( sc->extinction > 0.0 )
2747  sc->molar_concentration = sc->signal_concentration / sc->extinction;
2748  }
2749 
2750 }

3432 // slot to update autoflowAnalysis record at fitmen stage && register manually updated triple
3433 void US_Analysis_auto::update_autoflowAnalysis_statuses ( QMap < QString, QString > & triple_info )
3434 {
3435  QString triple_curr_key = triple_info[ "triple_name_key" ];
3436  QString requestID = triple_info[ "requestID" ];

3439  QStringList triple_name_parts = triple_curr_key.split(".");
3440  QString channel_name = triple_name_parts[0] + "." + triple_name_parts[1];
3441

3443 
3444

3446  QString FMB_changed = triple_info. contains( "FMB_changed" ) ? triple_info[ "FMB_changed" ] : QString("");
3447

3449 
3450  /* HOW to add && APPEND JSON in the DB ********
3451 
3452  1. If field is empty, first add initial record:
3453  UPDATE autoflowStatus set analysis='[{"2 / A / 260": "changed"}]' where ID=22;
3454 
3455  2. If not empty (then and after)
3456  UPDATE autoflowStatus set analysis=JSON_ARRAY_APPEND(analysis, '$', JSON_OBJECT('2 / B / 260', 'NO')) where ID=22;
3457  **********************************************/
3458 
3459  //Update autoflowStatus's 'analysis' field: per-channel (reference triple) basis, by whom:
3460  US_Passwd pw;
3461  US_DB2* dbP = new US_DB2( pw.getPasswd() );
3462 
3463  record_or_update_analysis_meniscus_status( dbP, triple_curr_key, FMB_changed );
3464 
3465 
3466 
3467  // Now update autoflowAnalysis records:
3468  QStringList requestID_list;
3469 
3470  if ( triple_curr_key.contains("Interference") )
3471  requestID_list << requestID;
3472  else
3473  requestID_list = Channel_to_requestIDs[ channel_name ];
3474 
3475  qDebug() << "Channel_name, requestIDs to update: " << channel_name << requestID_list;
3476 
3477 
3478 
3479  // --- Before updating autoflowAnalysis records ---
3480  // --- MAKE sure that ALL original 2DSA stages for other wavelength in a channel (besides representative wvl) are completed
3481  // --- i.e. are in WAIT status
3482  update_autoflowAnalysis_status_at_fitmen( dbP, requestID_list );
3483 
3484  //Restart timer:
3485  connect(timer_update, SIGNAL(timeout()), this, SLOT( gui_update ( ) ));
3486  timer_update->start(5000);
3487 
3488  qDebug() << "Timer restarted after updating EditProfiles for channel -- " << channel_name;
3489 }

3550 {

3558

3560  {

3563  return;

3572  db->next();

3576  QString lname = db->value( 2 ).toString();
3577  QString email = db->value( 4 ).toString();
3578  int level = db->value( 5 ).toInt();

3589

3594  // analysisJson += "\"" + analysisTriple + "\":\"" + analysisAction + "\"";
3595  // analysisJson += "}]";

3598  {

3600  qry << "update_autoflowStatusAnalysisFitmen_record"
3601  << QString::number( autoflowStatusID )
3602  << QString::number( autoflowID_passed )
3603  // << analysisJson //ALEXEY: not needed with new proc.
3604  << analysisTriple
3605  << analysisAction;
3606 
3607  db->query( qry );
3608  }
3609  else
3610  {

3645 // Check FITMEN | FITMEN_AUTO status before calling FITMEN constructor OR processing automatically
3646 bool US_Analysis_auto::check_fitmen_status( const QString& requestID, const QString& stageName )
3647 {
3648  bool status = false;
3649 
3650  US_Passwd pw;
3651  US_DB2 dbP( pw.getPasswd() );
3652 
3653  // Get the buffer data from the database
3654  if ( dbP.lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )
3655  {
3656  QMessageBox::warning( this, tr( "Connection Problem" ),
3657  tr( "Could not connect to database \n" ) + dbP.lastError() );
3658  return status;
3659  }
3660 
3661  QMap <QString, QString> analysis_details;
3662 
3663  analysis_details = read_autoflowAnalysis_record( &dbP, requestID );
3664 
3665  qDebug() << "In check_fitmen 1: -- " << requestID << stageName;
3666 
3667  if ( !analysis_details.size() )
3668  {
3669  //no record, so analysis completed/cancelled and already in the autoflowAnalysisHistory
3670 
3671  QMessageBox::information( this,
3672  QString( tr( "%1 | Triple Analysis already processed" ) ).arg( stageName ),
3673  QString( tr( "It appears that %1 stage has already been processed by "
3674  "a different user from different session and "
3675  "the entire analysis for the current triple is completed. \n\n"
3676  "The program will return to the autoflow runs dialog where "
3677  "you can re-attach to the actual current stage of the run. ")).arg( stageName ) );
3678 
3679  status = true;
3680  }
3681  else
3682  {
3683  //there is an autoflowAnalysis record:
3684 
3685  QString status_gen = analysis_details["status"];
3686  QString nextWaitStatus = analysis_details[ "nextWaitStatus" ] ;
3687  QString status_json = analysis_details["status_json"];
3688 
3689  qDebug() << "In check_fitmen 2: -- "
3690  << status_gen << "\n"
3691  << nextWaitStatus << "\n"
3692  << status_json ;
3693 
3694  QJsonDocument jsonDoc = QJsonDocument::fromJson( status_json.toUtf8() );
3695  if (!jsonDoc.isObject())
3696  {
3697  qDebug() << stageName << ": NOT a JSON Doc !!";
3698  status = true;
3699  }
3700 
3701  const QJsonValue &submitted = jsonDoc.object().value("submitted");
3702 
3703  //look for FITMEN | FITMEN_AUTO stage in "submitted" stages
3704  QString stage_name = submitted.toString();
3705 
3706  qDebug() << "In check_fitmen 3: -- "
3707  << submitted.toString() << stageName;
3708 
3709  if ( submitted.toString() == stageName )
3710  {
3711  qDebug() << "In check_fitmen 4: ";
3712 
3713  if ( status_gen != "WAIT" )
3714  {
3715  qDebug() << "In check_fitmen 5: ";
3716 
3717  QMessageBox::information( this,
3718  QString( tr( "%1 already processed" )).arg( stageName ),
3719  QString( tr( "It appears that %1 stage has already been processed by "
3720  "a different user from different session.\n\n"
3721  "The program will return to ANALYSIS tab where "
3722  "you can continue to monitor the overall analysis progress." )).arg( stageName ) );
3723 
3724  status = true;
3725  }
3726  }
3727  else
3728  {
3729  qDebug() << "In check_fitmen 6: ";
3730  //FITMEN | FITMEN_AUTO is no in "submitted" stages anymore, so it's processed:
3731  QMessageBox::information( this,
3732  QString( tr( "%1 already processed" )).arg( stageName ),
3733  QString( tr( "It appears that %1 stage has already been processed by "
3734  "a different user from different session.\n\n"
3735  "The program will return to ANALYSIS tab where "
3736  "you can continue to monitor the overall analysis progress." )).arg( stageName ) );
3737 
3738  status = true;
3739  }
3740  }
3741 
3742  return status;
3743 }

3745 //reset Analysis GUI: stopping all update processes
3746 void US_Analysis_auto::reset_analysis_panel( )
3747 {
3748  if ( autoflow_expType != "ABDE" || autoflow_expType == "VELOCITY" )
3749  {
3750  //Stop timer if active
3751  if ( timer_update -> isActive() )
3752  {
3753  timer_update -> stop();
3754  disconnect(timer_update, SIGNAL(timeout()), 0, 0);
3755 
3756  qDebug() << "Stopping timer_update !!!!";
3757  }
3758 
3759  //ALEXEY: now we should wait for completion of the last timer_update shot...
3760  connect(timer_end_process, SIGNAL(timeout()), this, SLOT( end_process ( ) ));
3761  timer_end_process->start(1000); // 5 sec
3762  }
3763  else
3764  {
3765  //add clearing ABDE-norm. GUI when switching btw. runs
3766 
3767 
3768  sdiag_norm_profile->hide();
3769  emit analysis_update_process_stopped();
3770  }
3771 }
3772 
3773 //Periodically check for ended processes
3774 void US_Analysis_auto::end_process( )
3775 {
3776  qDebug() << "In the END process: in_reload_end_processes = " << in_reload_end_process;
3777 
3778  if ( in_reload_end_process ) // If already doing a reload,
3779  return; // skip starting a new one
3780 
3781  in_reload_end_process = true; // Flag in the midst of a reload
3782 
3783  if ( !in_gui_update )
3784  {
3785 
3786  timer_end_process->stop();
3787  disconnect(timer_end_process, SIGNAL( timeout() ), 0, 0); //Disconnect timer from anything
3788 
3789  qDebug() << "ANALYSIS UPDATE panel has been reset!";
3790  qDebug() << "AFTER: in_gui_update: " << in_gui_update;
3791 
3792  reset_auto();
3793  qApp->processEvents();
3794 
3795  in_reload_end_process = false;
3796 
3797  emit analysis_update_process_stopped();
3798  }
3799  else
3800  {
3801  in_reload_end_process = false;
3802  qApp->processEvents();
3803  }
3804 }

3960 // Read AutoflowAnalysisRecord
3961 QMap< QString, QString> US_Analysis_auto::read_autoflowAnalysis_record( US_DB2* db, const QString& requestID )
3962 {
3963  QMap <QString, QString> analysis_details;
3964 
3965  // if ( db->lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK )

3974  << requestID;

3989  analysis_details[ "currentHPCARID" ] = db->value( 7 ).toString();
3990  analysis_details[ "status_json" ] = db->value( 8 ).toString();
3991  analysis_details[ "status" ] = db->value( 9 ).toString();
3992  analysis_details[ "status_msg" ] = db->value( 10 ).toString();
3993  analysis_details[ "create_time" ] = db->value( 11 ).toString();
3994  analysis_details[ "update_time" ] = db->value( 12 ).toString();
3995  analysis_details[ "create_userd" ] = db->value( 13 ).toString();
3996  analysis_details[ "update_user" ] = db->value( 14 ).toString();

3998  analysis_details[ "nextWaitStatusMsg" ] = db->value( 16 ).toString();
3999  }
4000  }

4003

4011

4239 //functions for FITMEN_AUTO stage
4240 void US_Analysis_auto::scan_dbase_auto( QMap <QString, QString> & triple_information )
4241 {
4242  QVector< ModelDesc > mDescrs; // Vector of model description objects
4243  US_Passwd pw; // DB password
4244  US_DB2 db( pw.getPasswd() ); // DB control
4245  QStringList query; // DB query string list
4246  QStringList mfnams; // List of FM model fit file names
4247  QStringList ufnams; // List of unique model fit file names
4248  QStringList uantms; // List of unique model fit analysis times
4249  QStringList tmodels; // List: IDs of models with truncated descrs
4250  QStringList tedGIDs; // List: edit GUIDs of models w/ trunc descrs
4251  QStringList tedIDs; // List: edit IDs of models w/ trunc descrs
4252  QList< int > botredo; // List: bottom-redo Mdescr vector
4253 
4254  int nfmods = 0; // Number of fit-meniscus models
4255  int nfsets = 0; // Number of fit-meniscus analysis sets
4256  int nfrpls = 0; // Number of fit file replacements
4257  int nfadds = 0; // Number of fit file additions
4258  int nfexss = 0; // Number of fit files left as they existed
4259 
4260  QString invID = triple_information[ "invID" ];
4261 
4262  QRegExp fmIter = QRegExp( "i\?\?-[mb]*",
4263  Qt::CaseSensitive, QRegExp::Wildcard );
4264 
4265  //QApplication::setOverrideCursor( QCursor( Qt::WaitCursor ) );
4266 
4267  // Scan the database and find fit-meniscus models
4268 
4269  // le_status->setText(
4270  // tr( "Scanning DB fit-meniscus models ..." ) );
4271 
4272  query << "get_model_desc_auto" << invID << triple_information[ "filename" ];
4273  // Make use of the description && '2DSA-FM'
4274  //query << "get_model_desc" << invID;
4275  db.query( query );
4276 
4277  while( db.next() )
4278  {
4279  ModelDesc mdescr;
4280  QString modelID = db.value( 0 ).toString();
4281  QString modelGUID = db.value( 1 ).toString();
4282  QString descript = db.value( 2 ).toString();
4283  QString editGUID = db.value( 5 ).toString();
4284  QString editID = db.value( 6 ).toString();
4285 
4286  if ( descript.length() == 80 )
4287  { // Truncated description: save ID and skip update for now
4288 DbgLv(1) << "DbSc: TRUNC: modelID" << modelID << "descr" << descript;
4289  tmodels << modelID;
4290  tedGIDs << editGUID;
4291  tedIDs << editID;
4292  continue;
4293  }
4294 
4295  double variance = db.value( 3 ).toString().toDouble();
4296  double meniscus = db.value( 4 ).toString().toDouble();
4297  double bottom = 0.0;
4298  QDateTime lmtime = db.value( 7 ).toDateTime();
4299  lmtime.setTimeSpec( Qt::UTC );
4300  QString ansysID = descript.section( '.', -2, -2 );
4301  QString iterID = ansysID .section( '_', -1, -1 );
4302 DbgLv(1) << "DbSc: modelID vari meni" << modelID << variance << meniscus
4303  << "ansysID" << ansysID << "iterID" << iterID;
4304 
4305  if ( ansysID.contains( "2DSA-F" ) || iterID.contains( fmIter ) )
4306  { // Model from meniscus fit, so save information
4307 
4308  // Format and save the potential fit table file name
4309  QString fitVals = iterID .section( '-', 1, 1 );
4310 DbgLv(1) << "DbSc: *FIT* " << descript << "fitVals" << fitVals;
4311  int fittype = 0; // no fit
4312  if ( fitVals.length() > 6 )
4313  fittype = 3; // meniscus+bottom fit
4314  else if ( fitVals.startsWith( "b" ) )
4315  fittype = 2; // bottom fit
4316  else if ( fitVals.startsWith( "m" ) )
4317  fittype = 1; // meniscus fit
4318  QString fextn = ( fittype != 2 ) ?
4319  ".fitmen.dat" : ".fitbot.dat";
4320 DbgLv(1) << "DbSc: fittype" << fittype << "fextn" << fextn;
4321  if ( fittype == 2 || fittype == 3 )
4322  { // Bottom or Meniscus+Bottom: add to list of bottom redo's
4323  botredo << mDescrs.count();
4324  }
4325  QString runID = descript.section( '.', 0, -4 );
4326  QString tripleID = descript.section( '.', -3, -3 );
4327  QString editLabel = ansysID .section( '_', 0, -5 );
4328  QString anType = ansysID .section( '_', 2, -3 );
4329 
4330 DbgLv(1) << "DbSc: anType" << anType << "editLabel" << editLabel << "ansysID" << ansysID;
4331  QString ftfname = runID + "/" + anType + "." + editLabel + "."
4332  + tripleID + fextn;
4333  mdescr.description = descript;
4334  mdescr.baseDescr = runID + "." + tripleID + "."
4335  + ansysID.section( "-", 0, 3 );
4336  mdescr.fitfname = ftfname;
4337  mdescr.modelID = modelID;
4338  mdescr.modelGUID = modelGUID;
4339  mdescr.editID = editID;
4340  mdescr.editGUID = editGUID;
4341  mdescr.variance = variance;
4342  mdescr.meniscus = meniscus;
4343  mdescr.bottom = bottom;
4344  mdescr.antime = descript.section( '.', -2, -2 )
4345  .section( '_', 1, 1 ).mid( 1 );
4346  mdescr.lmtime = lmtime;
4347 
4348  mDescrs << mdescr;
4349  } // END: model is fit type
4350  } // END: database model record reads
4351 DbgLv(1) << "DbSc: tmodels size" << tmodels.size() << "ted sizes"
4352  << tedGIDs.size() << tedIDs.size();
4353 
4354  // Review models with truncated descriptions
4355  for ( int ii = 0; ii < tmodels.size(); ii++ )
4356  {
4357  QString modelID = tmodels[ ii ];
4358  query.clear();
4359  query << "get_model_info" << modelID;
4360  db.query( query );
4361 
4362  if ( db.lastErrno() != US_DB2::OK ) continue;
4363 
4364  db.next();
4365 
4366  QString modelGUID = db.value( 0 ).toString();
4367  QString descript1 = db.value( 1 ).toString();
4368  QString contents = db.value( 2 ).toString();
4369  int jdx = contents.indexOf( "description=" );
4370 //DbgLv(1) << "DbSc: ii jdtx" << ii << jdtx << "modelID" << modelID
4371 // << " dsc1" << descript1 << " cont" << contents.left( 20 );
4372 
4373  if ( jdx < 1 ) continue;
4374 
4375 //DbgLv(1) << "DbSc: jdx lend" << jdx << lend;
4376  QString descript = contents.mid( jdx ).section( '"', 1, 1 );
4377  double variance = db.value( 3 ).toString().toDouble();
4378  double meniscus = db.value( 4 ).toString().toDouble();
4379  QString editGUID = tedGIDs[ ii ];
4380  QString editID = tedIDs [ ii ];
4381 
4382  QDateTime lmtime = db.value( 6 ).toDateTime();
4383  lmtime.setTimeSpec( Qt::UTC );
4384  QString ansysID = descript.section( '.', -2, -2 );
4385  QString iterID = ansysID .section( '_', -1, -1 );
4386 //DbgLv(1) << "DbSc: dscr1" << descript1 << "dcs" << descript;
4387 
4388  if ( ansysID.contains( "2DSA-F" ) || iterID.contains( fmIter ) )
4389  { // Model from meniscus fit, so save information
4390 DbgLv(1) << "DbSc: *FIT* " << descript;
4391  ModelDesc mdescr;
4392  double bottom = 0.0;
4393 
4394  // Format and save the potential fit table file name
4395  QString runID = descript.section( '.', 0, -4 );
4396  QString tripleID = descript.section( '.', -3, -3 );
4397  QString editLabel = ansysID .section( '_', 0, -5 );
4398  QString fitVals = iterID .section( '-', 1, 1 );
4399  int fittype = 0;
4400  if ( fitVals.length() > 6 )
4401  fittype = 3;
4402  else if ( fitVals.startsWith( "b" ) )
4403  fittype = 2;
4404  else if ( fitVals.startsWith( "f" ) )
4405  fittype = 1;
4406  QString fextn = ( fittype != 2 ) ?
4407  ".fitmen.dat" : ".fitbot.dat";
4408 
4409  if ( fittype != 1 )
4410  { // Bottom or Meniscus+Bottom: add to list of bottom redo's
4411  botredo << mDescrs.count();
4412  }
4413 
4414  QString anType = ansysID .section( '_', 2, -3 );
4415 
4416  QString ftfname = runID + "/" + anType + "." + editLabel + "."
4417  + tripleID + fextn;
4418  mdescr.description = descript;
4419  mdescr.baseDescr = runID + "." + tripleID + "."
4420  + ansysID.section( "-", 0, 3 );
4421  mdescr.fitfname = ftfname;
4422  mdescr.modelID = modelID;
4423  mdescr.modelGUID = modelGUID;
4424  mdescr.editID = editID;
4425  mdescr.editGUID = editGUID;
4426  mdescr.variance = variance;
4427  mdescr.meniscus = meniscus;
4428  mdescr.bottom = bottom;
4429  mdescr.antime = descript.section( '.', -2, -2 )
4430  .section( '_', 1, 1 ).mid( 1 );
4431  mdescr.lmtime = lmtime;
4432 
4433  mDescrs << mdescr;
4434  }
4435  }
4436 
4437  // Redo any model descriptions that need a bottom value
4438  for ( int ii = 0; ii < botredo.count(); ii++ )
4439  {
4440  int jj = botredo[ ii ];
4441  ModelDesc mdescr = mDescrs[ jj ];
4442  QString modelID = mdescr.modelID;
4443  US_Model wmodel;
4444  wmodel.load( modelID, &db );
4445  double bottom = wmodel.bottom;
4446 
4447  if ( bottom < 1.0 )
4448  { // Bottom not reliable in model, get from model description
4449  QString descript = mdescr.description;
4450  QString ansysID = descript.section( '.', -2, -2 );
4451  QString iterID = ansysID .section( '_', -1, -1 );
4452  QString fitVals = iterID .section( '-', 1, 1 );
4453  int fittype = 0; // no fit
4454  if ( fitVals.length() > 6 )
4455  fittype = 3; // meniscus+bottom fit
4456  else if ( fitVals.startsWith( "b" ) )
4457  fittype = 2; // bottom fit
4458  else if ( fitVals.startsWith( "m" ) )
4459  fittype = 1; // meniscus fit
4460  bottom = ( fittype == 2 ) ?
4461  ( fitVals.mid( 1, 5 ).toDouble() / 10000.0 ) :
4462  ( fitVals.mid( 6, 5 ).toDouble() / 10000.0 );
4463  }
4464 
4465  mdescr.bottom = bottom;
4466  mDescrs[ jj ] = mdescr;
4467  }
4468 
4469  nfmods = mDescrs.count();
4470 DbgLv(1) << "Number of FM models found: " << nfmods;
4471 if(nfmods>0) {
4472 DbgLv(1) << " pre:D0" << mDescrs[0].description;
4473 DbgLv(1) << " pre:Dn" << mDescrs[nfmods-1].description; }
4474  qSort( mDescrs );
4475 if(nfmods>0) {
4476 DbgLv(1) << " sorted:D0" << mDescrs[0].description;
4477 DbgLv(1) << " sorted:Dn" << mDescrs[nfmods-1].description; }
4478 
4479  // Scan local files to see what fit table files already exist
4480 
4481  // le_status->setText(
4482  // tr( "Comparing to existing local meniscus,rmsd table files ..." ) );
4483  mfnams.clear();
4484  ufnams.clear();
4485  uantms.clear();
4486 
4487  for ( int ii = 0; ii < nfmods; ii++ )
4488  { // Find unique file names in order to create sets
4489  QString ftfname = mDescrs[ ii ].fitfname;
4490  QString antime = mDescrs[ ii ].antime;
4491 
4492  if ( ! ufnams.contains( ftfname ) )
4493  { // This is a new fit-file name, so new analysis set
4494  ufnams << ftfname;
4495  uantms << antime;
4496  }
4497 
4498  else if ( ! uantms.contains( antime ) )
4499  { // Already seen fit-file, but new analysis time, so duplicate
4500  uantms << antime;
4501  }
4502 
4503  mfnams << mDescrs[ ii ].fitfname;
4504  }
4505 
4506  nfsets = ufnams.size();
4507  int nantm = uantms.size();
4508  int ndupl = nantm - nfsets;
4509 DbgLv(1) << "Number of FM analysis sets: " << nfsets;
4510 DbgLv(1) << "Number of FM analysis set duplicates: " << ndupl;
4511  int kfsets = nfsets;
4512  QString rdir = US_Settings::resultDir().replace( "\\", "/" ) + "/";
4513  QString fnamesv;
4514 
4515  for ( int ii = 0; ii < kfsets; ii++ )
4516  { // Find out for each set whether a corresponding fit file exists
4517  QString ftfname = ufnams.at( ii );
4518 
4519  if ( mfnams.count( ftfname ) == 1 )
4520  { // Not really a set; single fit model after previous fm run
4521  nfsets--;
4522 DbgLv(1) << "ScDB: SINGLE:" << ftfname;
4523  continue;
4524  }
4525 
4526  QString ftfpath = rdir + ftfname;
4527  QFile ftfile( ftfpath );
4528 
4529  if ( ftfile.exists() )
4530  { // File exists, so we must check the need to replace it
4531  QString ftfpath = rdir + ftfname;
4532  QDateTime fdate = QFileInfo( ftfile ).lastModified().toUTC();
4533  int jj = mfnams.lastIndexOf( ftfname );
4534  QDateTime rdate = mDescrs[ jj ].lmtime;
4535 DbgLv(1) << " ii rdate fdate" << ii << rdate << fdate << " ftfname"
4536  << ftfname << " fdate.msecsTo(rdate)" << fdate.msecsTo(rdate);
4537 DbgLv(1) << " jj desc" << jj << mDescrs[jj].description
4538  << "antime meniscus" << mDescrs[jj].antime << mDescrs[jj].meniscus;
4539 
4540  if ( fdate.msecsTo( rdate ) > 0 )
4541  { // DB record date is later than file date, so must replace file
4542  nfrpls++;
4543  ftfile.remove();
4544  }
4545 
4546  else
4547  { // DB record date is not later than file date, so leave file as is
4548  nfexss++;
4549  continue;
4550  }
4551  }
4552 
4553  else
4554  { // File does not exist, so we definitely need to create it
4555  nfadds++;
4556  QString ftfpath = QString( rdir + ftfname ).section( "/", 0, -2 );
4557  DbgLv(1) << "ScDB: NOT-EXIST local: nfadds" << nfadds << "ftfpath: " << ftfpath;
4558  QDir().mkpath( ftfpath );
4559  }
4560 
4561  if ( ! ftfile.open( QIODevice::WriteOnly | QIODevice::Text ) )
4562  { // Problem!!!
4563  qDebug() << "*ERROR* Unable to open file" << ftfname;
4564  continue;
4565  }
4566 
4567  // Creating a new or replacement file: build list of meniscus,rmsd pairs
4568  int jfirst = mfnams.indexOf( ftfname );
4569  int jlast = mfnams.lastIndexOf( ftfname ) + 1;
4570  QString antiml = mDescrs[ jlast - 1 ].antime;
4571  QStringList mrpairs;
4572 
4573 DbgLv(1) << " Creating" << ftfname << "jf,jl" << jfirst << jlast;
4574  for ( int jj = jfirst; jj < jlast; jj++ )
4575  { // First build the pairs (or triples) list
4576  double bottom = mDescrs[ jj ].bottom;
4577  double meniscus = mDescrs[ jj ].meniscus;
4578  double variance = mDescrs[ jj ].variance;
4579  double rmsd = sqrt( variance );
4580  QString antime = mDescrs[ jj ].antime;
4581  QString mrpair = QString::number( meniscus, 'f', 6 ) + " "
4582  + QString::number( rmsd, 'e', 6 );
4583 
4584  if ( bottom > 1.0 )
4585  { // Either Bottom or Meniscus+Bottom
4586  if ( ftfname.contains( "FB" ) )
4587  { // Bottom only
4588  mrpair = QString::number( bottom, 'f', 6 ) + " "
4589  + QString::number( rmsd, 'e', 6 );
4590  }
4591  else
4592  { // Meniscus and Bottom
4593  mrpair = QString::number( meniscus, 'f', 6 ) + " "
4594  + QString::number( bottom, 'f', 6 ) + " "
4595  + QString::number( rmsd, 'e', 6 );
4596  }
4597  }
4598 DbgLv(1) << " jj desc" << jj << mDescrs[jj].description;
4599 
4600  if ( antime == antiml )
4601  mrpairs << mrpair;
4602  }
4603 
4604  mrpairs.sort();
4605  QTextStream ts( &ftfile );
4606 
4607  // Output the pairs to the file
4608  for ( int jj = 0; jj < mrpairs.size(); jj++ )
4609  ts << mrpairs.at( jj ) + "\n";
4610 
4611  ftfile.close();
4612 
4613  fnamesv = fnamesv.isEmpty() ? ftfname : fnamesv;
4614  }
4615 
4616 DbgLv(1) << "Number of FM REPLACE sets: " << nfrpls;
4617 DbgLv(1) << "Number of FM ADD sets: " << nfadds;
4618 DbgLv(1) << "Number of FM EXISTING sets: " << nfexss;
4619 
4620  // Report
4621  QString msg = tr( "File" );
4622  int nftota = nfadds + nfrpls;
4623 
4624  if ( nfadds == 1 && nfrpls == 0 )
4625  msg += tr( " added: " );
4626 
4627  else if ( nfadds == 0 && nfrpls == 1 )
4628  msg += tr( " updated: " );
4629 
4630  else if ( nfadds == 0 && nfrpls == 0 )
4631  msg = tr( "No new fit files were created." );
4632 
4633  else
4634  msg = tr( "Last of %1 added/updated: " ).arg( nftota );
4635 
4636  if ( nftota > 0 )
4637  msg += fnamesv;
4638 
4639  //le_status->setText( msg );
4640  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
4641  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
4642 
4643  qDebug() << "End of scan auto:";
4644

4870 //Load data from text_content
4871 void US_Analysis_auto::load_data_auto( const QString& text_content )
4872 {
4873  int count = 0;
4874  QString contents = text_content;
4875  contents.replace( QRegExp( "[^0-9eE\\.\\n\\+\\-]+" ), " " );
4876 
4877  QStringList lines = contents.split( "\n", QString::SkipEmptyParts );
4878  QStringList parsed;
4879  v_meni.clear();
4880  v_bott.clear();
4881  v_rmsd.clear();
4882  bott_fit = fname_load.contains( "fitbot" );
4883 DbgLv(1) << "LD: bott_fit" << bott_fit << "fname_load" << fname_load;
4884 
4885  for ( int ii = 0; ii < lines.size(); ii++ )
4886  {
4887  QStringList values = lines[ ii ].split( ' ', QString::SkipEmptyParts );
4888

4890 DbgLv(1) << "LD: ii" << ii << "valsize" << valsize;
4891 
4892  if ( valsize < 2 ) continue;
4893 
4894  if ( valsize > 3 )
4895  {
4896  values.removeFirst();
4897  valsize--;
4898  }
4899 
4900  double rmeni = values[ 0 ].toDouble();
4901  double rbott = values[ 1 ].toDouble();
4902  double rmsdv = rbott;
4903 
4904  if ( rmeni < 5.0 || rmeni > 8.0 ) continue;
4905 
4906  count++;
4907 
4908  if ( valsize == 3 )
4909  {
4910  rmsdv = values[ 2 ].toDouble();
4911  v_meni << rmeni;
4912  v_bott << rbott;
4913  v_rmsd << rmsdv;
4914 
4915  parsed << QString().sprintf( "%3d : ", count ) +
4916  QString::number( rmeni, 'f', 5 ) + ", " +
4917  QString::number( rbott, 'f', 5 ) + ", " +
4918  QString::number( rmsdv, 'f', 8 );
4919 
4920  }
4921 
4922  else if ( valsize == 2 )
4923  {
4924  v_meni << rmeni;
4925  v_rmsd << rmsdv;
4926 
4927  parsed << QString().sprintf( "%3d : ", count ) +
4928  QString::number( rmeni, 'f', 5 ) + ", " +
4929  QString::number( rmsdv, 'f', 8 );
4930  }
4931  }
4932 
4933  bool was3val = have3val;
4934  have3val = ( v_bott.count() > 0 );
4935  //te_data->e->setPlainText( parsed.join( "\n" ) );
4936 DbgLv(1) << "LD: was3val have3val" << was3val << have3val
4937  << "v_rmsd size" << v_rmsd.size() << "parsed length"
