4946 //process 2d data
4947 void US_Analysis_auto::process_2d( void )
4948 {
4949  int count = v_meni.count();
4950  double* radius_values = v_meni.data();
4951  double* rmsd_values = v_rmsd.data();
4952 
4953  double minx = 1e20;
4954  double maxx = 0.0;
4955 
4956  double miny = 1e20;
4957  double maxy = 0.0;
4958 
4959  // Remove any non-data lines and put values in arrays
4960  for ( int ii = 0; ii < count; ii++ )
4961  {
4962  // Find min and max
4963  minx = qMin( minx, radius_values[ ii ] );
4964  maxx = qMax( maxx, radius_values[ ii ] );
4965 
4966  miny = qMin( miny, rmsd_values[ ii ] );
4967  maxy = qMax( maxy, rmsd_values[ ii ] );
4968  }
4969 
4970  if ( count < 3 ) return;
4971 
4972  double overscan = ( maxx - minx ) * 0.10; // 10% overscan
4973 
4974  // meniscus_plot->setAxisScale( QwtPlot::xBottom,
4975  // minx - overscan, maxx + overscan );
4976 
4977  // Adjust y axis to scale all the data
4978  double dy = fabs( maxy - miny ) / 10.0;
4979  dy_global = dy;
4980 
4981  //meniscus_plot->setAxisScale( QwtPlot::yLeft, miny - dy, maxy + dy );
4982 
4983  // raw_curve = us_curve( meniscus_plot, tr( "Raw Data" ) );
4984  // raw_curve->setPen ( QPen( Qt::yellow ) );
4985  // raw_curve->setSamples( radius_values, rmsd_values, count );
4986 
4987  // Do the fit and get the minimum
4988 
4989  double c[ 10 ];
4990 
4991  //int order = sb_order->value();
4992  int order = 2; //ALEXEY ---------------------------------------------------------> How order is passed??
4993 
4994  if ( ! US_Matrix::lsfit( c, radius_values, rmsd_values, count, order + 1 ) )
4995  {
4996  QMessageBox::warning( this,
4997  tr( "Data Problem" ),
4998  tr( "The data is inadequate for this fit order" ) );
4999 
5000  // le_men_fit ->clear();
5001  // le_bot_fit ->clear();
5002  // le_mprads ->clear();
5003  // le_rms_error ->clear();
5004  // meniscus_plot->replot();
5005 
5006  return;
5007  }
5008 
5009  int fit_count = (int) ( ( maxx - minx + 2 * overscan ) / 0.001 );
5010 
5011  QVector< double > vfitx( fit_count );
5012  QVector< double > vfity( fit_count );
5013  double* fit_x = vfitx.data();
5014  double* fit_y = vfity.data();
5015  double x = minx - overscan;
5016 
5017  for ( int i = 0; i < fit_count; i++, x += 0.001 )
5018  {
5019  fit_x[ i ] = x;
5020  fit_y[ i ] = c[ 0 ];
5021 
5022  for ( int j = 1; j <= order; j++ )
5023  fit_y[ i ] += c[ j ] * pow( x, j );
5024  }
5025 
5026  // Calculate Root Mean Square Error
5027  double rms_err = 0.0;
5028 
5029  for ( int i = 0; i < count; i++ )
5030  {
5031  double x = radius_values[ i ];
5032  double y = rmsd_values [ i ];
5033 
5034  double y_calc = c[ 0 ];
5035 
5036  for ( int j = 1; j <= order; j++ )
5037  y_calc += c[ j ] * pow( x, j );
5038 
5039  rms_err += sq ( fabs ( y_calc - y ) );
5040  }
5041 
5042  //le_rms_error->setText( QString::number( sqrt( rms_err / count ), 'e', 5 ) );
5043 
5044  // Find the minimum
5045  if ( order == 2 )
5046  {
5047  // Take the derivitive and get the minimum
5048  // c1 + 2 * c2 * x = 0
5049  fit_xvl = - c[ 1 ] / ( 2.0 * c[ 2 ] );
5050  }
5051  else
5052  {
5053  // Find the zero of the derivative
5054  double dxdy [ 9 ];
5055  double d2xdy2[ 8 ];
5056 
5057  // First take the derivitive
5058  for ( int i = 0; i < order; i++ )
5059  dxdy[ i ] = c[ i + 1 ] * ( i + 1 );
5060 
5061  // And we'll need the 2nd derivitive
5062  for ( int i = 0; i < order - 1; i++ )
5063  d2xdy2[ i ] = dxdy[ i + 1 ] * ( i + 1 );
5064 
5065  // We'll do a quadratic fit for the initial estimate
5066  double q[ 3 ];
5067  US_Matrix::lsfit( q, radius_values, rmsd_values, count, 3 );
5068  fit_xvl = - q[ 1 ] / ( 2.0 * q[ 2 ] );
5069 
5070  const double epsilon = 1.0e-4;
5071 
5072  int k = 0;
5073  double f;
5074  double f_prime;
5075  do
5076  {
5077  // f is the 1st derivative
5078  f = dxdy[ 0 ];
5079  for ( int i = 1; i < order; i++ ) f += dxdy[ i ] * pow( fit_xvl, i );
5080 
5081  // f_prime is the 2nd derivative
5082  f_prime = d2xdy2[ 0 ];
5083  for ( int i = 1; i < order - 1; i++ )
5084  f_prime += d2xdy2[ i ] * pow( fit_xvl, i );
5085 
5086  if ( fabs( f ) < epsilon ) break;
5087  if ( k++ > 10 ) break;
5088 
5089  // Get the next estimate
5090  fit_xvl -= f / f_prime;
5091 
5092  } while ( true );
5093  }
5094 
5095  // fit_curve = us_curve( meniscus_plot, tr( "Fitted Data" ) );
5096  // fit_curve->setPen ( QPen( Qt::red ) );
5097  // fit_curve->setSamples( fit_x, fit_y, fit_count );
5098 
5099 
5100  // copy miny to global variables
5101  miny_global = miny;
5102 
5103  // Plot the minimum
5104 
5105  // minimum_curve = us_curve( meniscus_plot, tr( "Minimum Pointer" ) );
5106  // minimum_curve->setPen( QPen( QBrush( Qt::cyan ), 3.0 ) );
5107 
5108  double radius_min[ 2 ];
5109  double rmsd_min [ 2 ];
5110 
5111  radius_min[ 0 ] = fit_xvl;
5112  radius_min[ 1 ] = fit_xvl;
5113 
5114  rmsd_min [ 0 ] = miny - 1.0 * dy;
5115  rmsd_min [ 1 ] = miny + 2.0 * dy;
5116 
5117  // minimum_curve->setSamples( radius_min, rmsd_min, 2 );
5118 
5119  // Display selected meniscus/bottom
5120  //le_men_sel->setText( QString::number( fit_xvl, 'f', 5 ) );
5121 
5122  // Find the "best-index", index where X closest to fit
5123  ix_best = 0;
5124  double diff_min = 1.0e+99;
5125 
5126  for ( int ii = 0; ii < v_meni.count(); ii++ )
5127  {
5128  double diff_x = qAbs( v_meni[ ii ] - fit_xvl );
5129 
5130  if ( diff_x < diff_min )
5131  { // Running least difference and index to it
5132  diff_min = diff_x;
5133  ix_best = ii;
5134  }
5135  }
5136 
5137 
5138  // // Add the marker label -- bold, font size default + 1, lines 3 pixels wide
5139  // QPen markerPen( QBrush( Qt::white ), 3.0 );
5140  // markerPen.setWidth( 3 );
5141 
5142  // QwtPlotMarker* pm = new QwtPlotMarker();
5143  // QwtText label( QString::number( fit_xvl, 'f', 5 ) );
5144  // QFont font( pm->label().font() );
5145  // QwtSymbol* sym = new QwtSymbol( QwtSymbol::Cross, QBrush( Qt::white ),
5146  // markerPen, QSize( 9, 9 ) );
5147 
5148  // font.setBold( true );
5149  // font.setPointSize( font.pointSize() + 1 );
5150  // label.setFont( font );
5151 
5152  // pm->setValue ( fit_xvl, miny + 3.0 * dy );
5153  // pm->setSymbol ( sym );
5154  // pm->setLabel ( label );
5155  // pm->setLabelAlignment( Qt::AlignTop );
5156 
5157  // pm->attach( meniscus_plot );
5158 
5159  // meniscus_plot->replot();
5160 }

5163 //process 3d data
5164 void US_Analysis_auto::process_3d( void )
5165 {
5166  bool auto_lim = false;
5167  double min_x = 1.0e+99;
5168  double min_y = 1.0e+99;
5169  double min_z = 1.0e+99;
5170  double max_x = -1.0e+99;
5171  double max_y = -1.0e+99;
5172  double max_z = -1.0e+99;
5173  double b_meni = 0.0;
5174  double b_bott = 0.0;
5175  int min_ix = -1;
5176 
5177  // Get minima,maxima and meniscus,bottom at best rmsd
5178  for ( int ii = 0; ii < v_meni.size(); ii++ )
5179  {
5180  double rmeni = v_meni[ ii ];
5181  double rbott = v_bott[ ii ];
5182  double rrmsd = v_rmsd[ ii ];
5183 
5184  // Find min and max
5185  min_x = qMin( min_x, rmeni );
5186  max_x = qMax( max_x, rmeni );
5187  min_y = qMin( min_y, rbott );
5188  max_y = qMax( max_y, rbott );
5189  max_z = qMax( max_z, rrmsd );
5190 
5191  if ( rrmsd < min_z )
5192  { // Save best-rmsd meniscus,bottom
5193  min_z = rrmsd;
5194  b_meni = rmeni;
5195  b_bott = rbott;
5196  min_ix = ii + 1;
5197  }
5198  }
5199  double min_r = 1.0 / max_z;
5200  double max_r = 1.0 / min_z;
5201 
5202  // // Report low-rmsd meniscus and bottom values
5203  // le_men_lor->setText( QString::number( b_meni, 'f', 5 ) );
5204  // le_bot_lor->setText( QString::number( b_bott, 'f', 5 ) +
5205  // " ( " +
5206  // QString::number( min_ix ) + " )" );
5207 DbgLv(1) << "pl3d: v_meni size" << v_meni.size() << "min,max x,yz"
5208  << min_x << max_x << min_y << max_y << min_z << max_z;
5209 
5210  // Compute and report fitted meniscus and bottom
5211 
5212  int nmeni = v_meni.count( v_meni[ 0 ] );
5213  int nbott = v_bott.count( v_bott[ 0 ] );
5214  ix_best = min_ix - 1;
5215  int ix_men = ix_best / nbott;
5216  int ix_bot = ix_best % nbott;
5217  QList< int > ixs;
5218 DbgLv(1) << "pl3d: nmeni nbott" << nmeni << nbott << "ix_best" << ix_best
5219  << "ix_men ix_bot" << ix_men << ix_bot;
5220 
5221  // Compute indexes for up to 9 points centered at best index.
5222  // Exclude some if center point is on edge(s).
5223  for ( int jmx = ix_men - 1; jmx < ix_men + 2; jmx++ )
5224  {
5225  if ( jmx < 0 || jmx >= nmeni ) // Skip out-of-bounds index
5226  continue;
5227 
5228  for ( int jbx = ix_bot - 1; jbx < ix_bot + 2; jbx++ )
5229  {
5230  if ( jbx < 0 || jbx >= nbott ) // Skip out-of-bounds index
5231  continue;
5232 
5233  ixs << ( jmx * nbott + jbx ); // Save full vector index
5234 DbgLv(1) << "pl3d: jmx jbx ixs" << jmx << jbx << (jmx*nbott+jbx);
5235  }
5236  }
5237 
5238  // Now calculate the weight averages of meniscus and bottom
5239  f_meni = 0.0;
5240  f_bott = 0.0;
5241  double w_rmsd = 0.0;
5242  for ( int ii = 0; ii < ixs.count(); ii++ )
5243  {
5244  int jx = ixs[ ii ];
5245  double f_rmsd = 1.0 / v_rmsd[ jx ] - min_r;
5246  f_meni += ( v_meni[ jx ] * f_rmsd );
5247  f_bott += ( v_bott[ jx ] * f_rmsd );
5248  w_rmsd += f_rmsd;
5249 DbgLv(1) << "pl3d: ixs" << jx << "f_meni f_bott w_rmsd"
5250  << f_meni << f_bott << w_rmsd;
5251  }
5252  f_meni /= w_rmsd;
5253  f_bott /= w_rmsd;
5254 DbgLv(1) << "pl3d: f_meni f_bott" << f_meni << f_bott;
5255 
5256  // le_men_fit->setText( QString::number( f_meni, 'f', 5 ) );
5257  // le_bot_fit->setText( QString::number( f_bott, 'f', 5 ) );
5258 }

5632  for ( int jj = 0; jj < nedtfs; jj++ )
5633  { // Modify each Edit file corresponding to a wavelength
5634  QString fn = filedir + "/" + edtfiles.at( jj );
5635 DbgLv(1) << " eupd: jj" << jj << "fn" << fn;
5636 
5637  // if ( auto_mode )
5638  // le_status->setText( "Updating edit profile: " + edtfiles.at( jj ) );
5639 
5640  QFile filei( fn );
5641 
5642  if ( ! filei.open( QIODevice::ReadOnly | QIODevice::Text ) )
5643  { // Skip any file we cannot read
5644 DbgLv(1) << " eupd: *OPEN ERROR*";
5645  continue;
5646  }
5647 
5648 DbgLv(1) << " eupd: edtext read";
5649  // Read in the Edit XML text
5650  QTextStream ts( &filei );
5651  edtext = "";
5652  while ( !ts.atEnd() )
5653  edtext += ts.readLine() + "\n";
5654  filei.close();
5655 DbgLv(1) << " eupd: edtext len" << edtext.length();
5656 
5657  // Compute locations and lengths of meniscus,bottom,data lines,values
5658  ixmlin = edtext.indexOf( "<meniscus radius=" );
5659  if ( ixmlin < 0 ) continue;
5660  ixmval = edtext.indexOf( "=\"", ixmlin ) + 2;
5661  ncmval = edtext.indexOf( "\"", ixmval + 1 ) - ixmval;
5662  ncmlin = edtext.indexOf( ">", ixmlin ) - ixmlin + 1;
5663  ixllin = edtext.indexOf( "<data_range left=" );
5664  if ( ixllin < 0 ) continue;
5665  ixlval = edtext.indexOf( "=\"", ixllin ) + 2;
5666  nclval = edtext.indexOf( "\"", ixlval + 1 ) - ixlval;
5667  lefval = edtext.mid( ixlval, nclval ).toDouble();
5668  ixblin = edtext.indexOf( "<bottom radius=" );
5669  if ( ixblin > 0 )
5670  {
5671  ixbval = edtext.indexOf( "=\"", ixblin ) + 2;
5672  ncbval = edtext.indexOf( "\"", ixbval + 1 ) - ixbval;
5673  ncblin = edtext.indexOf( ">", ixblin ) - ixblin + 1;
5674  }
5675 DbgLv(1) << " eupd: ixmlin ixblin ixllin" << ixmlin << ixblin << ixllin;
5676 
5677  if ( mennew >= lefval ) //ALEXEY: HERE !!!
5678  {
5679  //cancel job && restart timer();
5680  fitmen_bad_vals = true;
5681  QString reason_for_failure = QString( "The selected Meniscus value, %1 , extends into the data range whose left-side value is %2")
5682  .arg( mennew )
5683  .arg( lefval );
5684 
5685  triple_information[ "failed" ] = reason_for_failure;
5686  delete_jobs_at_fitmen( triple_information );
5687 
5688  return; //ALEXEY - if one wvl in a triple fails, ALL fail!!!
5689  //continue;
5690  }
5691 
5692  demval = s_meni.length() - ncmval; // Deltas in old,new value strings
5693  debval = s_bott.length() - ncbval;
5694 
5695  if ( have3val )
5696  { // Replace meniscus and bottom values in edit
5697  edtext.replace( ixmval, ncmval, s_meni );
5698  ncmval += demval;
5699  ncmlin += demval;
5700  if ( ixbval > 0 )
5701  { // Replace an existing bottom line
5702  ixbval += demval;
5703  edtext.replace( ixbval, ncbval, s_bott );
5704  ixblin += demval;
5705  ncbval += debval;
5706  ncblin += debval;
5707  }
5708  else
5709  { // Must insert an entirely new line for bottom
5710  QString bline = QString( "\n <bottom radius=\"" )
5711  + s_bott + QString( "\"/>" );
5712  ixblin = ixmlin + ncmlin;
5713  edtext.insert( ixblin, bline );
5714  ncblin = bline .length();
5715  ncbval = s_bott.length();
5716  }
5717 DbgLv(1) << " eupd: 3DVL replace";
5718  }
5719  else if ( !bott_fit )
5720  { // Replace meniscus value in edit
5721  edtext.replace( ixmval, ncmval, s_meni );
5722  ncmval += demval;
5723  ncmlin += demval;
5724 DbgLv(1) << " eupd: MENI replace";
5725  }
5726  else
5727  { // Replace bottom value in edit
5728  if ( ixbval > 0 )
5729  {
5730  edtext.replace( ixbval, ncbval, s_bott );
5731  ncbval += debval;
5732  ncblin += debval;
5733  }
5734  else
5735  { // Must insert an entirely new line for bottom
5736  QString bline = QString( "\n <bottom radius=\"" )
5737  + s_bott + QString( "\"/>" );
5738  ixblin = ixmlin + ncmlin;
5739  edtext.insert( ixblin, bline );
5740  ncblin = bline .length();
5741  ncbval = s_bott.length();
5742  }
5743 DbgLv(1) << " eupd: BOTT replace";
5744  }
5745 
5746 DbgLv(1) << " eupd: write: fn" << fn;
5747  // Write out the modified Edit XML file
5748  QFile fileo( fn );
5749 
5750  if ( ! fileo.open( QIODevice::WriteOnly | QIODevice::Text ) )
5751  continue;
5752 
5753  QTextStream tso( &fileo );
5754  tso << edtext;
5755  fileo.close();
5756 
5757  // If using DB, update the edit record there
5758 
5759  if ( db_upd )
5760  {
5761 
5762  if (progress_msg_fmb != NULL )
5763  {
5764  progress_msg_fmb->setValue( jj );
5765  }
5766 
5767 DbgLv(1) << " eupd: call upd_db_ed";
5768  update_db_edit( edtext, fn );
5769 DbgLv(1) << " eupd: ret fr upd_db_ed idEdit" << idEdit;
5770 
5771  if ( edtfiles[ jj ] == fname_edit )
5772  idEdsv = idEdit;
5773  }
5774 
5775  } // END: wavelengths loop
5776 DbgLv(1) << " eupd: idEdit idEdsv" << idEdit << idEdsv;
5777  idEdit = idEdsv;
5778 DbgLv(1) << " eupd: idEdit" << idEdit;
5779 
5780  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
5781  QApplication::restoreOverrideCursor();
5782 
5783 
5784 
5785  } // END: apply to all wavelengths
5786 
5787  if ( rmv_mdls )
5788  {
5789  DbgLv(1) << " call Remove Models";
5790  remove_models_auto( triple_information[ "invID" ] );
5791  }
5792 
5793 
5794 
5795  //Set progress to max
5796  if ( progress_msg_fmb != NULL )
5797  {
5798  progress_msg_fmb->setValue( progress_msg_fmb->maximum() ); //ALEXEY -- bug fixed..
5799  progress_msg_fmb->close();
5800  }
5801 
5802  update_autoflowAnalysis_statuses( triple_information );
5803  //emit editProfiles_updated( triple_information );
5804  //close();
5805 
5806 }

5808 // Update the DB edit record with a new meniscus and/or bottom value
5809 void US_Analysis_auto::update_db_edit( QString edtext, QString efilepath )
5810 {
5811  int elnx = edtext.indexOf( "<editGUID " );
5812  int esvx = edtext.indexOf( "\"", elnx ) + 1;
5813  int nvch = edtext.indexOf( "\"", esvx ) - esvx;
5814  QString edGUID = edtext.mid( esvx, nvch );
5815 DbgLv(1) << "updDbEd: edGUID" << edGUID;
5816 
5817  US_Passwd pw;
5818  US_DB2 db( pw.getPasswd() );
5819  QStringList query;
5820  query << "get_editID" << edGUID;
5821  db.query( query );
5822  db.next();
5823  idEdit = db.value( 0 ).toString().toInt();
5824 DbgLv(1) << "updDbEd: idEdit" << idEdit;
5825  if ( db.writeBlobToDB( efilepath, "upload_editData", idEdit ) != US_DB2::OK )
5826  {
5827  qDebug() << tr( "*ERROR* update_db_edit: " ) << db.lastError();
5828  //msg += tr( "*ERROR* update_db_edit: " );
5829  //msg += db.lastError();
5830  return;
5831  }
5832 
5833 
5834  return;
5835 }

6412 // Set the fit models index for set fit meniscus/bottom
6413 void US_Analysis_auto::index_model_setfit()
6414 {
6415  if ( have3val )
6416  { // Fit Mensicus + Bottom: find closest x,y in list
6417  // double xmeni = le_men_fit->text().toDouble();
6418  // double ybott = le_bot_fit->text().toDouble();
6419 
6420  double xmeni = f_meni;
6421  double ybott = f_bott;
6422 
6423  double lowxyd = 1.0e+99;
6424 DbgLv(1) << "IMS: xmeni ybott" << xmeni << ybott;
6425 
6426  for ( int ii = 0; ii < v_meni.count(); ii++ )
6427  { // Find lowest difference in X,Y list
6428  double xydiff = sq( ( xmeni - v_meni[ ii ] ) ) +
6429  sq( ( ybott - v_bott[ ii ] ) );
6430  xydiff = ( xydiff == 0.0 ) ? 0.0 : sqrt( xydiff );
6431 
6432  if ( xydiff < lowxyd )
6433  { // Save lowest difference so far and its index
6434  ix_setfit = ii;
6435  lowxyd = xydiff;
6436 DbgLv(1) << "IMS: ii" << ii << "lowxyd" << lowxyd;
6437  }
6438  }
6439  }
6440 
6441  else
6442  { // Fit Meniscus OR Fit Bottom: find close X in list
6443  //double xselec = le_men_sel->text().toDouble();
6444 
6445  double xselec = fit_xvl;
6446 
6447  double lowxd = 1.0e+99;
6448 DbgLv(1) << "IMS: xselec" << xselec << "v_meni count" << v_meni.count();
6449 
6450  for ( int ii = 0; ii < v_meni.count(); ii++ )
6451  { // Find lowest difference in X list
6452  double xdiff = qAbs( ( xselec - v_meni[ ii ] ) );
6453 
6454  if ( xdiff < lowxd )
6455  { // Save lowest difference so far and its index
6456  ix_setfit = ii;
6457  lowxd = xdiff;
6458 DbgLv(1) << "IMS: ii" << ii << "lowxd" << lowxd << "v_meni-ii" << v_meni[ii];
6459  }
6460  }
6461  }
6462 DbgLv(1) << "IMS: ix_setfit" << ix_setfit;
6463 
6464  return;
6465 }

6468 // Create lists of information for noises that match a sample model from a set
6469 void US_Analysis_auto::noises_in_edit( QString modDesc, QStringList& nieDescs,
6470  QStringList& nieIDs, QStringList& nieFnams, QString invID )
6471 {
6472  QString msetBase = modDesc.section( ".", 0, -3 ) + "." +
6473  modDesc.section( ".", -2, -2 ).section( "_", 0, 3 );
6474  QString srchTlab = msetBase.section( ".", -2, -2 );
6475  QString srchTrip = srchTlab.left( 1 ) + "." + srchTlab.mid( 1, 1 ) + "." +
6476  srchTlab.mid( 2 ) + ".xml";
6477  QString srchRun = msetBase.section( ".", 0, -3 ) + "." +
6478  msetBase.section( ".", -1, -1 )
6479  .section( "_", 0, 0 ).mid( 1 );
6480 DbgLv(1) << "NIE: msetBase" << msetBase;
6481  if ( msetBase.contains( "2DSA-FM-IT" ) )
6482  {
6483  msetBase = msetBase.replace( "2DSA-FM-IT", "2DSA-FM" );
6484  }
6485  if ( msetBase.contains( "2DSA-FB-IT" ) )
6486  {
6487  msetBase = msetBase.replace( "2DSA-FB-IT", "2DSA-FB" );
6488  }
6489  if ( msetBase.contains( "2DSA-FMB-IT" ) )
6490  {
6491  msetBase = msetBase.replace( "2DSA-FMB-IT", "2DSA-FMB" );
6492  }
6493 DbgLv(1) << "NIE: msetBase" << msetBase;
6494  QStringList query;
6495  QString fname;
6496  QString noiID;
6497  int nlnois = 0;
6498  bool db_upd = true;
6499 //*DEBUG*
6500 //db_upd=false;
6501 //*DEBUG*
6502 
6503  QStringList noifilt;
6504  noifilt << "N*.xml";
6505  QString noidir = US_Settings::dataDir() + "/noises";
6506  QStringList noifiles = QDir( noidir ).entryList(
6507  noifilt, QDir::Files, QDir::Name );
6508  noidir = noidir + "/";
6509 DbgLv(1) << "NIE: noise-files-size" << noifiles.size();
6510 
6511  for ( int ii = 0; ii < noifiles.size(); ii++ )
6512  {
6513  QString noiFname = noifiles.at( ii );
6514  QString noiPath = noidir + noiFname;
6515  US_Noise noise;
6516 
6517  if ( noise.load( noiPath ) != US_DB2::OK )
6518  continue; // Can't use if can't load
6519 
6520  QString noiDesc = noise.description;
6521 DbgLv(1) << "NIE: ii noiDesc" << ii << noiDesc;
6522 
6523  if ( ! noiDesc.startsWith( msetBase ) )
6524  continue; // Can't use if not from the model set
6525 
6526  nlnois++;
6527 
6528  nieDescs << noiDesc;
6529  nieFnams << noiPath;
6530 DbgLv(1) << "NIE: noiFname" << noiFname;
6531 
6532  if ( ! db_upd )
6533  nieIDs << "-1";
6534  }
6535 
6536  if ( db_upd )
6537  {
6538  US_Passwd pw;
6539  US_DB2 db( pw.getPasswd() );
6540  QStringList nIDs;
6541 
6542  //QString invID = QString::number( US_Settings::us_inv_ID() );
6543 
6544  QStringList edtIDs;
6545  QStringList edtNams;
6546 
6547  query.clear();
6548  query << "all_editedDataIDs" << invID;
6549  db.query( query );
6550 
6551  while( db.next() )
6552  {
6553  QString edtID = db.value( 0 ).toString();
6554  QString edtName = db.value( 2 ).toString();
6555 
6556  if ( edtName.startsWith( srchRun ) &&
6557  edtName.endsWith( srchTrip ) )
6558  {
6559  edtIDs << edtID;
6560  edtNams << edtName;
6561 DbgLv(1) << "NIE: edtID edtName" << edtID << edtName;
6562  }
6563  }
6564 DbgLv(1) << "NIE: edtIDs-size" << edtIDs.size();
6565 if ( edtIDs.size() > 0 ) DbgLv(1) << "NIE: edtName0" << edtNams[0];
6566 
6567  query.clear();
6568 
6569  if ( edtIDs.size() == 1 )
6570  query << "get_noise_desc_by_editID" << invID << edtIDs[ 0 ];
6571 
6572  else
6573  query << "get_noise_desc" << invID;
6574 
6575  db.query( query );
6576 
6577  while( db.next() )
6578  {
6579  QString noiID = db.value( 0 ).toString();
6580  QString edtID = db.value( 2 ).toString();
6581 DbgLv(1) << "NIE: noiID edtID" << noiID << edtID;
6582 
6583  if ( edtIDs.contains( edtID ) )
6584  nIDs << noiID;
6585  }
6586 DbgLv(1) << "NIE: nIDs-size" << nIDs.size() << "msetBase" << msetBase;
6587 
6588  for ( int ii = 0; ii < nIDs.size(); ii++ )
6589  {
6590  QString noiID = nIDs[ ii ];
6591  US_Noise noise;
6592 
6593  if ( noise.load( noiID, &db ) != US_DB2::OK )
6594  continue; // Can't use if can't load
6595 
6596  QString noiDesc = noise.description;
6597 DbgLv(1) << "NIE: ii noiID noiDesc" << ii << noiID << noiDesc;
6598 
6599  if ( ! noiDesc.startsWith( msetBase ) )
6600  continue; // Can't use if not from the model set
6601 
6602  nieIDs << noiID;
6603 
6604  if ( nlnois == 0 )
6605  {
6606  nieFnams << "";
6607  nieDescs << noiDesc;
6608  }
6609  }
6610  }
6611 DbgLv(1) << "NIE: db_upd" << db_upd << "nlnois" << nlnois
6612  << "nieDescs-size" << nieDescs.size() << "nieIDs-size" << nieIDs.size();
6613 
6614  return;
6615 }
